VALUES
(125, 3, 'Zucchini Noodles or Zoodles', 3, 'en', 'United States', 'An ingenious way to replace pasta with!', '<p><strong>The art of tasty zucchini noodles is to not heat them for too long if you do they will have a mushy consistency. Another important factor is that the zucchini is hard but not overripe. </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut up zucchini into thin noodles using a knife, vegetable peeler or a spiralizer. Then pick one of five ways to prepare your noodles.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>In soups</strong><br />Zucchini noodles are perfect in soups; just add them towards the last 3 minutes of your soup&rsquo;s cook time.<br /><br /><strong> Oven baked</strong><br />Place parchment paper on an oven safe baking sheet or oven rack and place the noodles on top. Make sure to spread them out so they cook evenly. Cook at 390 F for about 5-10 minutes or until they are heated.<br /><br /><strong>Raw</strong><br />Goes well in salads, or with pesto sauce or any other cold dressings over. <br /><br /><strong> Saute</strong><br />This is my favorite way to enjoy zucchini noodles. Spray a frying pan with non-stick spray or a few tablespoons with broth over medium heat. When the pan is hot, add the zucchini and cook for 5-7 minutes while tossing them with pasta tongs.</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Microwave</span><br /></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Microwave 1 minute if using one-two servings. Anything more than that you should microwave in 30-second intervals checking to see if done.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2018', '125.jpeg', '125_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2018-02-11', NULL, '16:45:20', 0, 0, 0, '', 1874, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:8505:7b00:190e:8cf1:c539:54f0', '', 'e8a4ad0e71fab484a68d3ebaf09147496e1dec43', '2021-02-04 21:32:48', 0, 1),
(126, 3, 'Turmeric Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Try this colorful oatmeal to jumpstart on your day. Turmeric is a wonderful spice because it has a natural anti-inflammatory effect. Black pepper helps the body absorb the active ingredient in turmeric (curcumin).', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water,&nbsp; turmeric, cinnamon, and a dash of pepper in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as shredded coconut, chopped nuts, ginger, honey, and fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong>I know it is weird with black pepper in your oatmeal, but you will not be able to taste it!&nbsp; I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=52&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference. </a>If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '126.jpg', '126_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-02-11', NULL, '16:59:02', 7, 0, 0, '', 1485, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:eda9:7d4:7a54:f056', '', 'ff1c038dafa338a08651fb8b4afc91e2c69b39a1', '2021-02-05 04:55:13', 0, 1),
(127, 3, 'Fried Tilapia with Chili', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious and quick way to make tilapia! Please note that chili powder is different from cayenne pepper.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine chili powder, garlic powder, and salt in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Rub tilapia with the spice mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add the tilapia and cook until done flipping once, about 4-7 minutes depending on the thickness of your fillets. The fish is finished if it flakes when you lightly press it with a fork.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with lime, a green salad, rice, and asparagus or green beans.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When you fry fish, it is advisable to keep it out of the refrigerator for 10-15 minutes so that the temperature in the pan does not change when it is cooked. Also, fry the fish with the side that did not have skin on first.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '127.jpg', '127_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-02-11', NULL, '20:43:31', 23, 0, 0, '', 1331, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:19ac:cbb:3c34:143e', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '1f92b6668118ab7516730cf57b544d665a60be65', '2021-02-04 20:23:34', 0, 1),
(131, 3, 'Tofu Tacos', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'No meat needed. Feel free to add 40 gram finely chopped mushroom per serving for a meat-like texture.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Press the tofu, if you do not know how follow<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=14&amp;l=en\"> this guide.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Crumble tofu and chop onions. Finely puree or add chipotle peppers to a mini food processor. Add to a skillet and let cook for 4-5 minutes.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\"><strong>Step 3</strong><br /><br />Add spices, tomato sauce, chipotle peppers, and lime into the skillet. Cook another 2 minutes. <br /><br />Serve in taco shells or mini tortillas. Top with your favorite taco toppings, I top mine with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=9&amp;l=en\">Quick Coleslaw Mix</a> and <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=38&amp;l=en\">Chipotle Yogurt Sauce</a>. Click on the names for the recipes.&nbsp;<br /><br />Taco Topping Ideas<br />- Fresh chopped cilantro <br />- Greek yogurt or sour cream<br />- Shredded Mexican cheese or <a href=\"../food/view_food.php?food_id=192&amp;l=en\">Queso Fresco Mexican cheese.</a>&nbsp;<br />- Avocado or Guacamole<br />- Green onions<br />- Sliced Jalapeno<br />- Salsa or pico de gallo<br />- Corn<br />- Sliced red cabbage<br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '131.jpg', '131_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2018-02-14', NULL, '21:36:47', 26, 0, 0, '', 2053, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7cdc:d45f:27a:f684', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '71684af7e8214bafe0ad2ab068676572f9c5676f', '2021-02-04 21:34:53', 0, 1),
(132, 3, 'Berlin Inspired Yogurt', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'For food cart style chicken. Feel free to add a serving miracle whip if you want a creamier consistency.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Wash, dry, and mince fresh parsley.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add everything to a small bowl, add water if the dressing is too thick.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=339&amp;l=en\">Goes great with Berlin D&ouml;ner Chicken, click here for the recipe.&nbsp;</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/3/3/2021', '132.jpg', '132_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-02-14', NULL, '22:01:25', 0, 0, 0, '', 1244, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c\n193.202.110.21\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd', '', '13cb5e87c8d6f5926161f88f0b391e61982e8c53', '2021-02-04 19:40:17', 0, 1),
(134, 3, 'Spaghetti Squash Pizza', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I have given up looking for low-calorie pizza dough. Instead, I am embracing spaghetti squash&#039;s unique ability to pick up flavors from any sauce. This recipe fulfills my cravings for pizza!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Roast the spaghetti squash. When it is done, use a fork to scoop out two servings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the vegetables.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>After the spaghetti squash is done, brown the ground beef in a skillet. When it is nearly done add the onions and bell peppers and cook until ground beef is fully cooked.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add spaghetti squash and sauce. Let simmer for 3-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with freshly chopped parsley or basil, green onions, cheese, sauteed mushrooms, ketchup, mustard, olives, or spinach. <br /><br />You can substitute ground beef for other meat like ground turkey or turkey pepperoni.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '134.jpeg', '134_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2018-02-14', NULL, '23:20:31', 1, 0, 0, '', 1405, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:4d24:1ffc:a3e7:d7c4', '', '8243421523b4d14b29c83515d95ac5496b84c69b', '2021-02-04 21:09:25', 0, 0),
(136, 3, 'Quick &amp; Easy Tikka Masala', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Full of flavor but lower in calories than your traditional Tikka Masala. If you feel like it is too mild you can add 1/8th teaspoons of cayenne pepper. Feel free to substitute tomato sauce for crushed tomatoes for a chunkier sauce.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop onion, garlic, cilantro, and chicken.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a medium saucepan with non-stick spray and cook the onions over medium heat for three minutes. Add the garlic and cook another two minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add chicken, tomatoes, milk, and all the spices except cilantro. Let simmer for 15-20 minutes or until the chicken is done.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>When the chicken is done, take the saucepan off the heat the cilantro, lemon juice, and yogurt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with&nbsp;rice, steamed broccoli, and Naan.&nbsp;<br /><br />I measure my yogurt out after step 3 and let it sit out on the kitchen counter so it becomes room temperature before adding it to the pan. If you add it while it is too cold or the tikka sauce is too hot it has a higher chance of curdling.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '136.jpg', '136_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-02-16', NULL, '04:00:17', 0, 0, 0, '', 1359, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:449a:e679:2d97:eac3\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4d8e:d9c:e0f6:7811\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:1959:c4f6:735e:243f', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6da736ff8b52679d45d62aa58ac2ecc58ec6ed42', '2021-02-04 21:03:49', 0, 0),
(137, 3, 'Skinny Cheesecake Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'This is one of my all-time favorite Oatmeal recipes. Oatmeal is a great breakfast or lunch because it has a low glycemic index, which helps to maintain glucose levels.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water,&nbsp; and cheesecake pudding powder in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for 6+ hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as graham crackers, banana, powdered peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong><br />I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick.<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=52&amp;l=en\"> See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '137.jpeg', '137_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2018-02-16', NULL, '04:10:58', 0, 0, 0, '', 1653, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5d7f:40f7:af2:b652', '', '6d54f0a1e6e5cde3f836b2ba8ad64820339938d8', '2021-02-05 04:49:54', 0, 1),
(140, 3, 'Peanut Butter Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'The trick to eating a giant bowl of peanut butter flavored oatmeal within your daily calorie budget is using powdered peanut butter.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water,&nbsp; and powdered peanut butter in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as marshmallows, banana, nuts, and cinnamon.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong><br />I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=52&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference. I</a>f you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '140.jpeg', '140_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2018-02-17', NULL, '15:06:11', 0, 0, 0, '', 1705, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n185.191.171.36', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:50b0:e459:70b8:6bd2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '4f3a12a7285e3d8b53a28adfe4b4dac0142141be', '2021-02-05 03:42:07', 0, 1),
(141, 3, 'Asian Coconut Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Asian flavors fusion together for a tasty and healthy dinner.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Seed and dice the tomato. Mince the garlic and ginger.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Combine sauce ingredients in a bowl and mix over shrimp. Let marinate for 15 minutes in the fridge.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Pour the shrimp and marinade into a skillet over medium-high heat. Let simmer for a minute or two. Add the spinach and tomatoes and cook until spinach<span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\"> starts to wilt, 30-60 seconds</span>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve over rice, cauliflower rice, or pasta.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipeDirectionsListItem\">If you are using raw shrimp, cook it in the frying pan after step 2 until it turns pink and is done about 3 minutes. Once done, take them out of the pan and let rest on a plate until step 4. </span>Be careful to not overcook them as shrimp cook quickly. They will turn pink and form a loose C shape when they are done. If they start curling to a tighter O shape they are overcooked.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '141.jpeg', '141_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2018-02-18', NULL, '01:44:43', 0, 0, 0, '', 1426, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f03e:c84c:3fc9:17e8', '', '225c5b822030247e6715a3d69f1ac8e71425392c', '2021-02-04 19:39:26', 0, 1),
(142, 3, 'Gingerbread Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'There is a famous Norwegian saying that fits with this dish, Christmas lasts all the way until Easter', '<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Make oatmeal the way you usually adding spices and molasses. Sweeten to taste.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2021', '142.jpg', '142_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-02-18', NULL, '01:59:22', 0, 0, 0, '', 1629, '2600:8802:2f90:500:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:500:989f:c7e:3a25:e6e4\n2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c\n2600:8802:2f90:300:449a:e679:2d97:eac3\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.25\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9534b54a735c981cccbf65b909a12992dda31242', '2021-02-24 23:58:20', 0, 1),
(153, 3, 'Quick pasta sauce', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'You do not have to buy pasta sauce for a quick dinner. Avoid pasta sauce from a supermarket with added sugar when you make it yourself.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop onions. Brown the ground beef in a skillet. Towards<span style=\"color: #626262;\"> the end of the cooking time, add onions.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the chopped tomatoes and spices.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Let simmer for 10 minutes while stirring occasionally. If the sauce dries up you can add some water to loosen it up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve ove<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=125&amp;l=en\">r zoodles</a> or pasta.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Top with a little grated parmesan and fresh chopped basil. <br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br />Cinnamon is optional, I love adding it to my tomato-based sauces because it gives the dish a Greek twist. The sauce is extra delicious with garlic, bell peppers, carrots, and mushrooms. If you think the sauce is too acidic, you can add one teaspoon of stevia, erythritol, or other sweeteners. </span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2018', '153.jpeg', '153_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2018-08-23', NULL, '11:19:32', 9, 0, 0, '', 1363, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n192.99.15.33\n2a01:4f8:200:54aa::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::\n2a01:4f8:190:81e5::2', 0, NULL, '81.166.21.244', '', 'b3535e510c08723d1a088a8a50727d04fa78cc14', '2021-02-04 21:07:19', 0, 0),
(154, 3, 'Caramelized banana, sugar free', 3, 'en', 'United States', 'Is great for topping on ice cream or oatmeal.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat a pan with non-stick spray.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the banana.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook 2-3 minutes on each side depending on the thickness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2021', '154.jpg', '154_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-09-01', NULL, '01:59:26', 7, 0, 0, '', 1802, '167.114.211.237\n2a01:4f8:200:6406::2\n158.69.243.99\n192.99.5.228\n2607:5300:60:3ee4::1\n2a01:4f8:201:6390::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::\n207.180.218.247\n2a01:4f8:140:2155::2', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd', '', 'c5bbd9c8321855f9f0e1fcc814aed90e681102d6', '2021-03-07 10:26:32', 0, 1),
(158, 3, 'Cinnamon Roll Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to make the glaze using 15 grams of cream cheese and a dash of milk for a more authentic flavor.', '<h2 style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff;\">Directions</h2>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 30px; color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Add cinnamon to your oatmeal and prepare it the way you usually do.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Create the glaze by combining all the ingredients. If using cream cheese allow it to soften and add a dash of milk to make it thin enough to use as a glaze.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">When your oatmeal is done create the butter glaze by microwaving the butter and adding sugar and a dash of cinnamon.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Top the oatmeal with the butter glaze and yogurt glaze.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff;\">I prepare my oats using the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #375962; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=52&amp;l=en\">Voluminous Oatmeal Trick. Read more about it here!</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2021', '158.png', '158_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-11-20', NULL, '07:32:07', 1, 0, 0, '', 1595, '167.114.211.237\n2a01:4f8:200:6406::2\n158.69.243.99\n192.99.5.228\n2607:5300:60:3ee4::1\n2a01:4f8:201:6390::2', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c', '', 'c709a1df06afbba4c8bf48fe546de95063abde19', '2021-03-07 10:27:46', 0, 1),
(162, 3, 'Chia Seed Pudding', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Chia seeds are high in protein, antioxidants, fiber, and omega 3. A great way to start your day!', '<ol>\r\n<li>Mix all the ingredients in a small pyrex or mason jar. Shake well.</li>\r\n<li>Leave in the fridge overnight.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Sweeten to taste and top with fresh berries, honey, granola, and/or nut butter.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Lasts 4 days in the fridge in an airtight container.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are many different flavor variations, some examples:&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"color: #626262;\">- 30-gram pumpkin puree and 0.5 teaspoon pumpkin spice mixed in.&nbsp;<br /></span>- Topped with strawberry and shredded coconut. <br />- Chocolate chips and 5-gram cocoa powder mixed in. <br />- Peanut butter and banana mixed in. Also works with honey.<br />- Mango, cardamom, and honey.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/3/3/2021', '162.jpg', '162_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-11-25', NULL, '20:04:04', 0, 0, 0, '', 1291, '2600:8802:2f90:500:c9de:64a8:c76c:d5b1\n2600:8802:2f90:500:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:190:81e5::2', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:500:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'dbd657179da2a6cf8f84411e9e5f2cd020666dfb', '2021-02-24 23:50:48', 0, 1),
(166, 3, 'Beef and Broccoli Stir-fry', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to substitute broccoli for other veggies like green beans.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mince the garlic. Chop broccoli and onion. Slice beef into thin strips.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a small glass bowl add water, soy sauce, rice vinegar, sugar, ginger, and pepper. Mix.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brown the beef in a pan until done, 3-6 minutes. Set aside and wipe down the pan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add sesame oil to the pan along with onion, garlic, and broccoli. Let cook for 5 minutes.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the beef and sauce mix to the pan. Cook until the beef is heated through and the sauce thickens, another 2-3 minutes. If the sauce is too watery you can add a teaspoon of cornstarch to thicken it.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with green scallions, toasted sesame seeds, and rice or a green salad.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2021', '166.jpg', '166_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-12-03', NULL, '17:36:05', 2, 0, 0, '', 1386, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a03:2880:ff:8::face:b00c\n79.160.26.221', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '67021c328dedbbf2a8a3d6eb28959ded25189384', '2021-02-04 19:38:54', 0, 1),
(168, 3, 'Chocolate Banana Mousse', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Great low calorie high protein dessert', '<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Whip egg white until white peak forms, 3-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Mash the frozen banana and add to egg whites along with the cocoa powder and sweeten to taste,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">I use half a teaspoon of monk fruit to sweeten mine.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2021', '168.jpg', '168_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-12-14', NULL, '20:56:50', 0, 0, 0, '', 1819, '167.114.211.237\n2a01:4f8:200:6406::2\n158.69.243.99\n192.99.5.228\n2607:5300:60:3ee4::1\n2a01:4f8:201:6390::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::\n207.180.218.247', 0, NULL, '2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e', '', 'eec937cdbc1c66e565d8f5cd603296cad6eaec21', '2021-03-07 10:29:23', 0, 1),
(171, 3, 'Skinny Maple Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'I love Better Oats Oatmeal Maple &amp; Brown Sugar but it never fills me up. So I&#039;ve created multiple maple oatmeals to create one similar in flavor but more filling :-)', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water, cinnamon, maple extract, and cinnamon in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for 6+ hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as brown sugar, chopped pecans, banana,&nbsp; fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong><br />I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=52&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '171.jpg', '171_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2018-12-14', NULL, '22:14:18', 0, 0, 0, '', 1299, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:190:81e5::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7412:356f:8bde:bf70', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2a62e5510bcadac7d6a18d858141b852c2da1295', '2021-02-04 21:09:22', 0, 1),
(174, 16, 'Agurk og Mynte salat', 5, 'no', 'Afghanistan', 'Deilig og oppfriskende salat!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 1</p>\r\n<p>Kutt agurken i tynne skiver, del den gjerne p&aring; siden slik at den blir kuttet i halvm&aring;ner.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 2</p>\r\n<p>Kutt r&oslash;dl&oslash;k i tynne skiver.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 3</p>\r\n<p>Finkutt mynte.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 4</p>\r\n<p>Bland sammen eddik, salt, pepper, mynte i en sk&aring;l. Tilsett mynte, r&oslash;dl&oslash;k og agurk.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Sett gjerne i kj&oslash;leskapet et par timer f&oslash;r servering.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/2/2018', '174.jpeg', '174_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2018-12-16', NULL, '22:24:20', 6, 0, 0, '0', 1198, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n79.160.26.221\n', 0, NULL, '81.166.21.244', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '650de32b3a2db5b106966ab4d70fd215cd36a165', '2021-02-05 02:45:33', 0, 1),
(175, 16, 'Sky Br&oslash;d', 5, 'no', 'Norway', 'Endelig en m&aring;te &aring; nyte br&oslash;dmat uten karbohydrater! Legg gjerne til forskjellige krydder som oregano, basilikum eller r&oslash;d pepperflak til eggeplommene.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 1</p>\r\n<p>Forvarm ovnen til 150&deg; C og dekk to bakeplater med bakepapir.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 2</p>\r\n<p>Separer eggehvitene i en bolle og eggeplommer i en annen. For best resultat, bruk en glass eller st&aring;l sk&aring;l for eggehvitene.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 3</p>\r\n<p>Pisk eggehvitene til stive topper danner seg, v<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: FacebookEmoji, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&aelig;</span><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: FacebookEmoji, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">r</span> t<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aring;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">modig da dette tar tid.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Legg Xanthan Gum mot slutten. Hvis du ikke har Xanthan Gum kan du bruke litt salt.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 4</p>\r\n<p>Tilsett yoghurt og krydder i eggeplommer og r&oslash;r sammen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 5</p>\r\n<p>Kombiner eggeplommene og eggehvitene forsiktig. Ikke bruk en elektrisk mikser, r<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;</span>r forsiktig med en slikkepinne til alt er kombinert.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 6</p>\r\n<p>Plasser seks skjer av blandingen p<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aring;</span>&nbsp;hver bakeplate (omtrent en spiseskje hver).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 7</p>\r\n<p>Spre blandingen ut i sirkler med en slikkepinne eller spiseskje til ca. 0.5 cm tykk.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Steg 8<br /><br />Bak i 30 minutter eller til de er gyldene. La de avavkj&oslash;le i en time f&oslash;r servering.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med ditt favorittp&aring;legg eller som hamburgerbr<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;d</span>.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/2/2018', '175.jpeg', '175_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2018-12-16', NULL, '22:44:37', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1431, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124', 0, NULL, '81.166.21.244', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '74345be9d5827a921e2a36b9e66dcf2c80b5fe21', '2021-02-05 02:45:34', 0, 1),
(185, 3, 'Coffee Light frappuccino', 7, 'no', '', 'Inspirert av Starbucks! Lager to store glass.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bland sammen alt i en blender og server!&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Xanthan gum hjelper for &aring; holde&nbsp;flytende v&aelig;ske tyktflytende og at konsistensen p&aring; drikken blir riktig. Xanthan gum har ingenting med smaken &aring; gj&oslash;re s&aring; du kan lage den uten, men frappuccinoen blir ikke like godt blandet. Annen melk kan &aring; brukes.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/7/3/2019', '185.jpeg', '185_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-01-21', NULL, '13:10:09', 0, 0, 0, '', 1186, '2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:200:54aa::2\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '81.166.21.244', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b403e7ab3dfa01f9550f779c19efb7c5c3ade64e', '2021-01-06 01:22:53', 0, 1),
(193, 3, 'English Muffin with Egg White &amp; Cheese', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Microwave your egg white for a quick breakfast or lunch. For more protein add a slice of turkey sausage or ham!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Toast the muffin to your liking.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour the egg white into a microwave safe dish that is the same size as the muffin.&nbsp; Add salt and pepper if you want.&nbsp; Microwave for 30-90 seconds depending on your microwave.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Assemble the muffin with spinach, egg white, and cheese.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a cup of soup or salad. Goes well with sliced tomato and a bit butter as well.&nbsp; <br /><br /><br />Feel free to use a bagel thin, sandwich thin, or bread instead of a muffin.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '193.jpeg', '193_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-02-28', NULL, '19:18:52', 1, 0, 0, '', 1266, '72.79.53.50\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:980:b041:bb0b:a0eb', '', '8c27307678b380b362443ae7dcc8f1f11990d2c3', '2021-03-06 11:12:01', 0, 1),
(195, 3, 'Apple Pie Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Dessert for breakfast that is healthy? Yes, please!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop the apple. Add apple and vanilla extract to the oatmeal and stir well. Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as chopped walnuts, banana, allspice, ground ginger, or brown sugar.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash salt in your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\">I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '195.jpeg', '195_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-08', NULL, '03:16:16', 0, 0, 0, '', 1419, '72.79.53.50\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4c64:f251:9716:4e70\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:a4a2:b93e:657e:14c8', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bb60ee4dc8ecd98c7f79ebdcac7a32f1050ae91a', '2021-03-06 11:11:41', 0, 1),
(198, 3, 'Skinny Pesto Chicken Soup', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'A tasty soup that literally makes itself in a slow cooker.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the vegetables, basil, and garlic.&nbsp; For the chicken, you can either chop it now or cook the entire breast and chop/shred it after the soup is cooked. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all the ingredients except for the parmesan in a two-quart slow cooker and stir.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover and cook for 3-4 hours on high or 7-8 hours on low.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop or shred the chicken breast if you cooked it as a whole and return to the soup. Stir in parmesan and serve. Add salt and pepper to taste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '198.jpg', '198_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-03-16', NULL, '01:59:24', 22, 0, 0, '', 864, '72.79.53.50\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5c89:9808:56c7:ca29', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'af0573e93d60ee57fa4dd47440d092b034ec132d', '2021-03-06 11:17:02', 0, 1),
(199, 3, 'Frozen Yogurt', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and high in protein. In the photo, I added a Fiber One Brownie and four crushed mini Oreo cookies.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Mix together the ingredients using a hand mixer on medium speed for a couple of minutes. This helps add air and volume to the ice cream.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Pour into a ready ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer\'s instructions.</p>\r\n<strong>If you do not have an ice cream maker you can use one of these three options. It will not yield the same result but still delicious:</strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Freeze the mixture until semi-frozen in \"blender friendly sizes\" and then use a blender to get the right consistency.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Freeze the mixture in a container that you stir every 30 minutes for around 2 hours.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Use ice cream bar molds</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '199.jpg', '199_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-03-16', NULL, '05:32:45', 0, 0, 0, '', 1737, '2600:1012:b152:ad86:c0e8:c018:e7db:db2f\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.15\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', '', '07839cd8a808b3cc0f0857ac47fc3e21e9bfb7a6', '2021-02-25 03:47:41', 0, 1),
(200, 3, 'Taco with spaghetti squash', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'One of my favorite dinners. Switch up your regular Friday tacos with this tasty and healthy recipe! Feel free to use ground turkey or chicken instead of ground beef.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Roast the spaghetti squash.&nbsp;When it is done, use a fork to scoop out two servings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>After the spaghetti squash is done, brown the ground beef in a skillet. Add water according to the package and two servings of the spice mix. If you use McCormick Taco Seasoning add 120 ml (0.5 cups) water and 9 gram (4 tsp) spice mix.&nbsp; Let simmer for 3-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the two servings of the spaghetti squash to the skillet and stir to combine with the ground beef.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with your favorite taco toppings. I use finely chopped romaine lettuce, bell peppers, cilantro, jalapeno, chopped green onions. Other ideas are Mexican shredded cheese, pico de gallo or salsa, avocado, lime, sour cream, or Greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '200.jpeg', '200_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-16', NULL, '22:47:43', 14, 0, 0, '', 1191, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:1012:b109:1ba6:4894:2a64:89c4:9a96\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f8e0:f1c7:d34:1805', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '0ea4c16b1fa04558510613d166f641168fbb1a1c', '2021-02-04 21:17:57', 0, 1),
(201, 3, 'Hot Cocoa Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Taste like hot cocoa, indulgent and healthy!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water,&nbsp; and cocoa (Dutch-processed) in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as marshmallows, banana, powdered peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong>I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. </span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '201.jpeg', '201_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-19', NULL, '16:26:14', 0, 0, 0, '', 1342, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:d0c3:149c:76cf:b777\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:40b:3010:cb92:e08d', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '23d1d035f9ac4cebca196f004c7f8c1e18969c38', '2021-02-04 20:31:55', 0, 1),
(202, 3, 'Berry Smoothie Bowl', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'The best smoothie bowls are dense like a bowl of healthy sorbet. This is an easy recipe for a smoothie bowl that only needs three ingredients!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut and freeze banana a few hours before making the smoothie bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place the ingredients in a blender and blend to a puree.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into a deep bowl and top with your favorite toppings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Tips for a better smoothie bowl:<br />- Add a tablespoon&nbsp; Greek yogurt for extra creaminess. <br />- Add sweeteners to your smoothie bowl as frozen fruits usually lose their sweetness.<br />- A good blender will make all the difference in the consistency of your smoothie bowl. Usually, the cheaper blenders will leave your smoothie bowl more chunky or grainy.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '202.jpeg', '202_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-22', NULL, '17:40:26', 0, 0, 0, '', 1152, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:50b0:e459:70b8:6bd2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '45fb71eb8900fbc540de35a4e58dadcda78e66fc', '2021-02-04 19:40:38', 0, 1),
(203, 3, 'Lemon and Dill Oven Baked Salmon', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Oven baked salmon is super healthy and so easy to make!', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat oven to 350 F.</li>\r\n<li>Spray an oven-safe pan with non-stick spray or line with aluminum foil/parchment paper.</li>\r\n<li>Finely chop garlic.</li>\r\n<li>Make the lemon marinade by mixing all the ingredients into a bowl.</li>\r\n<li>Place the salmon into the pan and coat the fillets with lemon marinade.<br />Bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes, depending on the thickness of your fillets. The salmon is done when it can easily be flaked with a fork.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with steamed vegetables and rice.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '203.jpeg', '203_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-23', NULL, '00:06:06', 24, 0, 0, '', 1011, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c40f:2a08:f1c0:3b36', '', '1aa15cbd9f0b1f8f6734d9ff28fc9f6c53c464be', '2021-02-04 20:46:33', 0, 1),
(204, 3, 'Red Bell Pepper Soup', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I love the simplicity of this soup. No need to roast, peel, and steam the bell pepper. Everything can be made in one pan, easy and delicious.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Remove the seeds from the bell pepper. Chop the bell pepper, onion, and garlic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Saut&eacute; the bell pepper, onion, and garlic in a pot for 10 min. I saut&eacute; mine in water, but you can use non-stick spray, butter, or oil. Remember that the overall caloric nutrition changes then.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add chicken stock and let simmer for 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Use an immersion blender or heat-safe blender to puree the soup and serve.&nbsp; Add salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a tablespoon of greek yogurt or sour cream stirred in. Top with fresh cilantro, chopped green onions, cheese, croutons, or bacon.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '204.jpeg', '204_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-23', NULL, '00:28:51', 0, 0, 0, '', 1085, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:449a:e679:2d97:eac3\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c40f:2a08:f1c0:3b36', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2811734006177e2e596eacb6472536cfa3f91d66', '2021-02-04 21:03:52', 0, 1)
")
