(205, 3, 'Jicama Fries', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Jicama has a neutral taste that soaks up flavors from spices. High in fiber and paleo, low carb, or keto friendly.', '<ol>\r\n<li>Peel and slice the&nbsp;jicama into thin matchsticks about 1/4 inches thick.</li>\r\n<li>Preheat air fryer to 400 F or oven to 400 F.</li>\r\n<li>In a large bowl mix together the spices and jicama. Spray canola oil (or other oil) on top and toss to evenly coat the jicama with spices and oil.</li>\r\n<li><strong><br />Oven<br /></strong>Place jicama strips in a single layer on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 30-45 minutes.<br /><br /><strong>Air fryer<br /></strong>Place the jicama strips in a single layer in the basket and cook for 20 minutes. Shake the basket or turn the jicama strips every 5 minutes.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve topped with green onions, freshly chopped parsley, ketchup, mustard, and parmesan cheese.&nbsp; If you like garlic add 1/4th teaspoon garlic and onion powder to the spice mix in step 3. For a spicy twist, add 1/4th teaspoon chili powder!<br /><br /><strong>For a potato fry-like texture boil the jicama strips for 10-15 minutes and pat dry before air frying.</strong></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '205.jpeg', '205_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-24', NULL, '04:47:57', 0, 0, 0, '', 1239, '2600:8802:2f90:500:b9b6:cc64:f7cf:4c4\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:1012:b100:d686:4551:6bfb:43c9:3106\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:4d24:1ffc:a3e7:d7c4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'eb3a71a2e4eed779a2b7514b3c598e761a0d4f16', '2021-02-09 01:47:46', 0, 1),
(206, 3, 'Skinny Mashed Cauliflower', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'A super-healthy and low-calorie substitute for mashed potatoes, rice or pasta. Top with chopped fresh chives and parmesan cheese.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the cauliflower into smaller pieces.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Boil the cauliflower in a saucepan with water until it gets tender, about 10 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour out the water and mash the cauliflower with a stick blender, blender, or by hand using a potato masher.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add milk and stir until you get desired consistency, I use 30 grams of non-fat milk. Season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can replace milk with water in step 4, use the same water that you boiled the cauliflower in. Goes well with some finely chopped garlic added in step 4 as well.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '206.jpeg', '206_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-24', NULL, '21:39:49', 0, 0, 0, '', 1046, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '0b95bdd0b49471e4bc34a1a629a0b6c8e36a1b70', '2021-02-04 21:09:23', 0, 1),
(207, 16, 'Brokkoli og Kylling Wok', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Wok er en genial m&aring;te &aring; legge til flere gr&oslash;nnsaker i dagen din. Rask, lett og velsmakende :-)', '<p>Bland sausens ingredienser i en liten bolle.</p>\r\n<p>Hakk kylling og brokkoli i tynne stykker. Finhakk hvitl<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;</span>k og ingef&aelig;r.</p>\r\n<p>Stek kylling i en panne til den er ferdig, ca 5 minutter. Ta ut kyllingen fra pannen og legg den p<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&aring; </span>en tallerken.</p>\r\n<p><strong>I </strong>samme panne stek hvitl<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;</span>k og ingef<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aelig;r </span>i ca 1 minutt. Legg til brokkoli og sausen. La steke i 2-3 minutter f<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&aring;</span>r du legger kyllingen tilbake. La steke til kylling er dekket i saus og gjennomvarm.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Server med ris eller squash nudler.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '207.jpg', '207_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-03-07', NULL, '01:45:50', 2, 0, 0, '0', 964, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4d8e:d9c:e0f6:7811\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:eda9:7d4:7a54:f056', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '35d0fe975dced6af7113617c4d248bbaf60029a8', '2021-02-05 02:47:39', 0, 1),
(208, 16, 'Buffalo Kylling', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Server som taco p&aring; tynne mais tortillas, som finger mat med selleri, eller over en salat.', '<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Bland ketchup og chili saus i en stor bolle</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Skj<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aelig;r</span>&nbsp;kylling til&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;</span>nsket st<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;r</span>relse, for eksempel striper eller kuber.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Stek kylling i en panne til den er ferdig, ca 5 minutter</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Bland kyllingen i bollen med chili-sausen til den er belagt. Tilsett salt og pepper etter smak.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Server med gresk yoghurt eller r<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;</span>mme, og selleripinner.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '208.jpeg', '208_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-03-12', NULL, '02:09:05', 1, 0, 0, '0', 1096, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:39bc:12e2:39f7:1ccb', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '64f555d02dcdc5b56c11e66de8326464a76d1df3', '2021-02-05 03:04:58', 0, 1),
(212, 3, 'Fried Tilapia with Turmeric', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Turmeric is a wonderful spice because it has a natural anti-inflammatory effect. Black pepper helps the body absorb the active ingredient in turmeric (curcumin). Tasty and healthy!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix the spice together in a bowl. Cover the fish with the spice mixture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat the oil over medium heat in a frying pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Fry the tilapia until it is golden and cooked through. For thin fillets, it takes about 1-2 minutes per side and thick fillets about 3-5 minutes per side. The fish is finished if it flakes when you lightly press it with a fork.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with rice, fresh vegetables, and grated carrots. <br /><br />When you fry fish, it is advisable to keep it out of the refrigerator for 10-15 minutes so that the temperature in the pan does not change when it is cooked. Also, fry the fish with the side that did not have skin on first.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '212.jpeg', '212_thumb_278x156.jpeg', '', '2019-03-26', NULL, '20:48:34', 7, 0, 0, '', 1130, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:44a:3ade:e5b9:35db', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6c350db7468361d02dafa52d5c157505f8eefc55', '2021-02-04 20:24:48', 0, 1),
(213, 3, 'Chipotle Chicken or Steak', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Make your own Chipotle bowl, salad, taco, or burrito at home.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop the chipotle pepper and garlic by hand or in a mini food processor.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix spices and chipotle pepper in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breast or steak with the paste.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry the meat for 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of it or until the internal temperature on the meat reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken in the fridge after coating it with the spice paste. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=361&amp;l=en\">Click here for the recipe without Chipotle Pepper In Adobo Sauce.</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '213.jpeg', '213_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-02-27', NULL, '00:39:04', 14, 0, 0, '', 2013, '2600:8802:2f90:500:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c\n2600:8802:2f90:300:1030:2d7d:5cee:a0e8\n193.202.110.21\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2', 0, NULL, '46.30.210.139', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '093c2287fa3df4adfcd988a7c8e4767914075e41', '2021-02-23 19:50:19', 0, 1),
(214, 3, 'Springtime Chicken Soup', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Soups are perfect for spring because now is the time for the freshest flavors of your garden goodness. Fresh dill provides that holiday feeling.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the vegetables.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat the oil in a soup pot over medium-high. Add bell peppers and cook for 3 minutes. Add green onions and garlic, cook for another 2 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add chicken stock, paprika, celery and bring to a boil. Once boiling reduces the heat and let simmer for 15-20 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add green beans, zucchini, and dill. Let simmer for 3-5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with 1/4th of a lime squeezed over into each bowl. Add pepper to taste.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '214.jpg', '214_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-03-28', NULL, '02:01:24', 0, 0, 0, '', 887, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5c89:9808:56c7:ca29', '', '753dc0e8e3dbb8c70c00f1b114c161a2b114b9f8', '2021-02-04 21:17:54', 0, 1),
(218, 3, 'Very Berry Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'On Friday&#039;s we wear pink! Instagram friendly and tasty oatmeal.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine oats, water, and berries in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for 6+ hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as maple syrup, chopped hazelnuts, bananas, or more berries. <br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash salt in your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /></strong><br />I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. </span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '218.jpg', '218_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-01', NULL, '00:58:10', 0, 0, 0, '', 1006, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:19ac:cbb:3c34:143e', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fee341a59554a9deaec478d2e20357ea9ce11b86', '2021-02-04 21:26:26', 0, 1),
(222, 3, 'Zucchini and Mushroom Chicken Stir Fry', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Craving Panda Express without going out and the excessive sodium? Look no further!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop zucchini, and mushroom. Grate garlic, and ginger. Cut chicken into thin bite-size pieces and coat with cornstarch.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make the sauce by combining soy sauce, sugar substitute, and rice vinegar in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat sesame oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until it is done, 3-5 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken. Set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add zucchini, and mushroom into the skillet. Let cook for 5 minutes. Add garlic and ginger and let cook for another minute.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add back the chicken and sauce. Cook until sauce thickens, about 2-3 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve over rice or cauliflower rice. Sprinkle over with sesame seeds.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '222.jpg', '222_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-02', NULL, '00:20:35', 2, 0, 0, '', 977, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4d8e:d9c:e0f6:7811\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7164:7899:b6cf:4ebc', '', 'b46f5a2cee7f525f8fac554006a9afb42917244e', '2021-02-04 21:26:23', 0, 1),
(223, 3, 'How To: Collard Wraps', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Substitute your boring tortilla for a fancy and low-calorie collard wrap instead. Better than lettuce leaves because collard leaves are larger, more sturdy and more flexible. Unlike lettuce wraps, they fold up without breaking. Can be eaten raw or boiled. Boiling them for 30 seconds makes them more flexible. Only 8 calories each leaf.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Wash the collards to remove grit or debris. Bring a large pot of water to boil and let simmer, add a dash salt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030217.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"655\" /><br /><br />Using a small knife such as a paring knife, remove the thick part of the middle stem so the stem is as flat as the rest of the collard leaf.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prepare an ice bath by filling a large bowl with cold water and ice cubes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030347.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1090\" /><br /><br />Drop each collard leaf into the simmering water for 30 seconds. The longer it is in the simmering water, the softer it becomes. Using a pair of tongs move the leaf into an ice bath for 10 seconds.<br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030412.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1015\" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030434.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1135\" /><br />Pat dry with a kitchen towel. Store between paper towels/parchment or wax paper in the fridge for three days. <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030454.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"728\" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Top it with your favorite ingredients and roll it up like a burrito. To cut in half use a serrated knife.&nbsp;<br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030616.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1158\" /><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030648.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1204\" /><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030709.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"1079\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The difference between boiled and raw collard leaves. Boiled on left, raw on right:</strong> <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019/3_190402030805.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"503\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '223.jpg', '223_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-02', NULL, '02:39:23', 0, 0, 0, '', 1064, '79.161.62.47\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7164:7899:b6cf:4ebc', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fe73b2c554d7b3609c2f61d863f50472c21a4dad', '2021-03-02 21:52:10', 0, 1),
(225, 3, 'Sliders with grilled pineapple', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious sliders! Grilled pineapple have a smoked sweetness while the lemon coleslaw balances the entire dish.', '<p><strong>Ketchup&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix together, lemon, apple vinegar, and ketchup. Set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Coleslaw</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Shred red cabbage, cut the spring onion, set aside 25 grams of spring onion for the sliders.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the lemon juice, apple vinegar, salt, and pepper in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix together red cabbage, 25 grams of spring onion, and the lemon dressing made in step 2.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Sliders</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix ground beef, 25 grams of chopped spring onions, salt, and pepper.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Form to 8 small burgers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Fry each burger over medium-high heat for 2-3 minutes before turning it over and fry until it is cooked, about 1-2 minutes. Move the ready sliders to a plate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Pineapple</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut up the pineapple into 8 thin rings or squares.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Cook for about 1-2 minutes in the same skillet as you cooked the burgers on one side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Then put together each slider with slider bread, brush on ketchup on the underside, have a slider on top, then a pineapple ring, and finally coleslaw over that. Bon Appetit!</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/89/2019', '225.jpg', '225_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-03', NULL, '04:49:17', 1, 0, 0, '', 826, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'f6365fccba030d0d769bd913390d26d769095a4e', '2021-02-04 21:09:25', 0, 1),
(227, 3, 'Broccoli Puree', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'This recipe is inspired by a restaurant I went to while visiting Norway. I had cod alongside with broccoli puree. The flavor was so simple yet sophisticated so I decided to duplicate the recipe. It goes well with white fish, salmon, pork, and chicken.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"3c9jd-0-0\">Bring a large pot with water to boil. Add a dash of salt. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop broccoli into smaller pieces, use the leaves and stems. <span data-offset-key=\"65rm-0-0\">Add broccoli to the boiling water. Let boil rapidly <strong>under a lid</strong> for 6-8 minutes.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"bvlk0-0-0\">Strain the water, but keep a small amount in case you want to make the puree thinner.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"bvlk0-0-0\">Mash the broccoli to a puree consistency with a blender that tolerates heat,&nbsp; an immersion blender, or by hand with a potato masher. Add salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with Tabasco and lime juice.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '227.jpg', '227_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-04', NULL, '05:01:11', 23, 0, 0, '', 1023, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n114.119.133.14\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bd9878dcbe684a01f9901daf5dc14ccf1c2d8bc9', '2021-02-04 19:41:25', 0, 1),
(228, 3, 'Pear &amp; Cardamom Oatmeal', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'I love cardamom. Growing up my grandma would make the most wonderful cardamom buns. This got me thinking, would the same spices work in my morning oatmeal? Oh Yes!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the ginger and grate or chop the pear. Combine oats, water,&nbsp; cardamom, ginger, and pear in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish. <br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once cooled leave in the fridge for a couple of hours or overnight.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy it hot or cold: re-heat it in the microwave for one-two minutes or if you enjoy a pudding-like consistency enjoy it cold. Sweeten with your favorite sweetener.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as walnuts, banana, peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.<br /><br /><span data-offset-key=\"5gmsc-0-0\"><strong>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your oatmeal. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></strong>I make my oatmeal using double the amount of water and cook time known as the&nbsp;voluminous oatmeal trick.<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\"> See this recipe for reference.</a> If you prefer your oats the regular way just follow the directions on how to cook the oats according to the package and add the other ingredients in order. <br /><br />Cardamom is a very powerful spice. Some might find the flavor overwhelming or soap-like if you use too much so you might want to start out with 1/8th of a teaspoon and work your way up.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '228.jpg', '228_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-04', NULL, '06:41:37', 23, 0, 0, '', 1059, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n185.191.171.34\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.156.144', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '910f0975dd04b358c2f987dd38e61842a1d041f7', '2021-02-04 20:50:37', 0, 1),
(229, 3, 'Shrimp, Green Beans and Gnocchi', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to use any Gnocchi. I used Trader Joe&#039;s famous Cauliflower Gnocchi in mine. You can substitute green beans for broccoli, bell pepper, or asparagus. Use fresh lemon juice for best result!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"562es-0-0\">Chop green beans and shallot.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"562es-0-0\">Cook gnocchi in a skillet for 6-10 minutes or according to directions on the package. Transfer to a plate once done.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4hktg\" data-offset-key=\"10u7f-0-0\">\r\n<div class=\"_1mf _1mj\" data-offset-key=\"10u7f-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"10u7f-0-0\">In the same skillet over medium-high heat, cook shallots for 1-2 minutes. Add green beans and broth, cook another 3-4 minutes. </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4hktg\" data-offset-key=\"c4u6g-0-0\">\r\n<div class=\"_1mf _1mj\" data-offset-key=\"c4u6g-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"c4u6g-0-0\">If using raw shrimp, add shrimp and let simmer until shrimp is done. About 3-4 minutes, it should turn pink. </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"4hktg\" data-offset-key=\"4g3ai-0-0\">\r\n<div class=\"_1mf _1mj\" data-offset-key=\"4g3ai-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"4g3ai-0-0\">If using pre-cooked shrimp, let green beans, shallots, and broth simmer for another 3 minutes. </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"f9d2a-0-0\">Add pre-cooked shrimp (if using), gnocchi, and lemon juice: let simmer until everything is heated through. Remove skillet from heat and sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Serve after the cheese has melted, 1-2 minutes.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with red peppers flakes, fresh basil, or parsley.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '229.jpg', '229_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-04', NULL, '23:10:26', 9, 0, 0, '', 1111, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.133.14', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'f0ef3f6935c217ee87607bf3d075d1e8096b590b', '2021-02-04 21:10:32', 0, 1),
(230, 3, 'Kung Pao Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Did you know that Kung Pao Chicken was traditionally made with leeks? Here in the US, we have grown accustomed to a version containing green onions instead. I do not use peanuts in my recipe, but feel free to add 50 gram chopped peanuts to yours along with the other vegetables. Bamboo shoots can be substituted with water chestnuts or omitted.', '<ol>\r\n<li>Chop up the green onions, garlic, and chicken. Drain bamboo shoots.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Make the sauce by combining the ingredients in a small bowl. Set aside.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Toss the chicken in the chicken marinade ingredients. If you have time, let marinate in the fridge for 30 minutes.&nbsp; Pan-fry over medium-high heat until the chicken is fully cooked.&nbsp; Set aside on a plate. </span></li>\r\n<li>In the same skillet slowly heat up the sauce and add the green onions, garlic, bamboo shoots.</li>\r\n<li>Add the chicken and toss to coat the sauce, cook until sauce thickens. About 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with steamed vegetables and rice.<br /><br />For a darker sauce, use dark soy sauce. You can substitute white wine for an equal amount of soy sauce.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '230.jpg', '230_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-06', NULL, '22:42:44', 2, 0, 0, '', 1482, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n81.167.38.198\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 1, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '5f05d97f8dcbc0214b14cac34dd1cb1f099c5dc7', '2021-02-04 20:34:35', 0, 1),
(231, 3, 'Green Beans in Air Fryer', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'A spicy and simple recipe that makes a great side dish.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trim ends off green beans and mince the garlic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Make the sauce by combining all the ingredients except green beans. Toss the green beans with the sauce and let stand for at least 5 minutes.&nbsp; If you have time let marinate for 30 minutes.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Place green beans in a single layer in the air fryer basket. Cook 10-15 minutes on 400 F. Shake the basket every 5 minutes for even cooking. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '231.jpg', '231_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-07', NULL, '00:32:37', 2, 0, 0, '', 904, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7412:356f:8bde:bf70', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b1ff620026130a211fc33a1715e2ac7caf4fb5aa', '2021-02-04 20:28:11', 0, 1),
(237, 90, 'Cucumber and Mint Salad', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious and refreshing salad', '<ol>\r\n<li>Cut the cucumber into thin slices, then divide it on the side so that it is cut into half-moons.</li>\r\n<li>Cut red onions into thin slices. Finely chop mint.</li>\r\n<li>Mix together vinegar, salt, pepper, mint in a small bowl. Then mix all ingredients together and serve. Can also be kept in the fridge for two-three days in an airtight container.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If you are making this ahead of time, salt and drain the cucumbers either in a paper towel or in a colander for 20 minutes. This step is necessary for the cucumber to stay crunchy and not add excess water into the vinegar dressing.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/90/2019', '237.jpg', '237_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-08', NULL, '03:40:26', 0, 0, 0, '', 1111, '167.114.211.237\n2a01:4f8:200:6406::2\n158.69.243.99\n192.99.5.228\n2607:5300:60:3ee4::1\n2a01:4f8:201:6390::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::\n207.180.218.247\n2a01:4f8:140:2155::2\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:eda9:7d4:7a54:f056', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '760b943e65ffa85248efd3b16e32c813e6824e82', '2021-03-07 10:32:24', 0, 1),
(241, 3, 'Chick-fil-A Grilled Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'The secret behind the tasty chicken at Chik-fil-A is a good brine and a thin chicken breast that allows the chicken breast to cook evenly.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine all ingredients in a bowl and let brine for 15-30 minutes. You can cover and put it in the fridge or leave it out to gain a lukewarm temperature that is ready for the grill/pan. After 15-30 minutes drain the liquid, let the chicken breast rest on a paper towel or in a colander for a minute or two.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a Market Salad<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=242&amp;l=en\"> (click for recipe)</a> or in a toasted whole wheat bun with lettuce, tomato, and cheese. <br /><br />Only 10% of the calories in the brine will be absorbed into the chicken breast so do not fear the teaspoon of brown sugar or orange juice. <br /><br />Ingredients in Chik-fil-A\'s chicken breast, the ones in bold are the ones in my recipe as well:<br />Seasoning [<strong>apple cider vinegar</strong>, soybean oil, yeast extract, <strong>salt</strong>, modified corn starch, palm oil, <strong>dehydrated garlic, dehydrated onion,</strong> corn maltodextrin, sea salt, natural flavor,<strong> sugar,</strong> <strong>chicken stock</strong>, cane molasses, chicken fat, <strong>spice,</strong> natural flavor {including smoke}, dextrose, <strong>lemon peel</strong>, citric acid, red bell pepper, <strong>orange juice concentrate</strong>, grape juice concentrate, natural flavor, <strong>paprika</strong>, <strong>vinegar</strong>, xanthan gum, ascorbic acid,]<br /><br /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '241.jpg', '241_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-11', NULL, '22:57:58', 0, 0, 0, '', 1065, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n185.191.171.43', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', '', '841b32666109cbeffc5180ed5235fc0d7318d6d4', '2021-02-04 20:41:21', 0, 1),
(242, 3, 'Market Salad by Chick-fil-A', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'This and the cool wrap is my favorite dish at Chik-fil-A. Unfortunately, it cost over 9 dollars so I will make my own!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut up the vegetables and fruit, mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with grilled <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=241&amp;l=en\">Chik-fil-A\'s grilled chicken breast (click for recipe)</a> and granola, cranberries, pecans, almonds, walnuts, roasted almonds, glazed pecans, and blue cheese. <br /><br />Chik-fil-A\'s ingredients for Market Salad: <br /><strong>Romaine lettuce</strong>, chicken, <strong>red and green</strong> <strong>apple, strawberries</strong>, Granola glycerate cranberries, pecans, almonds, walnuts, green <strong>cabbage</strong>, <strong>blueberries</strong>, roasted almonds, glazed pecans, blue cheese, <strong>red leaf lettuce</strong>, green leaf lettuce.<br /><br />If you are making this recipe ahead of time I suggest reading SeriousEats article on how to prevent your apples from browning here: <a href=\"https://www.seriouseats.com/2015/09/how-to-prevent-apple-pear-browning.html\">https://www.seriouseats.com/2015/09/how-to-prevent-apple-pear-browning.html</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '242.jpg', '242_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-12', NULL, '01:01:53', 0, 0, 0, '', 967, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.8\n185.191.171.33\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::\n114.119.136.113', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9cd52ba93d86a8c1cb1fcea5b3081a56b376248f', '2021-02-04 20:40:56', 0, 1),
(243, 3, 'Tartar Sauce with Greek Yogurt', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to substitute some of the yogurts with mayo. You can also add finely chopped capers and as herbs like dill and parsley.', '<p>Chop onion and pickles. Mix everything together and let stand in the fridge for one hour before serving.</p>\r\n<p>Because this is made without mayo I\'d recommend using a higher fat Greek yogurt, but the non-fat one works as well.&nbsp; In addition, you might want to add sweeteners such as a small amount of honey or Splenda.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '243.jpg', '243_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-13', NULL, '05:12:26', 0, 0, 0, '', 1072, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:449a:e679:2d97:eac3\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.132.146', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd4e:229f:fd28:65ba', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c7f1395293b0db1247af05fe9f2db0f9d27c0bd0', '2021-02-04 21:26:13', 0, 1),
(244, 3, 'Lean Fish for Fish &amp; Chips', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'No breadcrumbs or flour needed in this recipe. A skinny version of your regular fish &amp; chips but still tasty. I&#039;d recommend using cod or haddock.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Separate egg yolk and the egg white in a glass bowl.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix spices with the egg yolk to form a paste, you can substitute parsley and marjoram for tarragon or omit them. Whip egg white by itself with an electric mixer until white peaks form, about 5 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Carefully fold the egg yolk paste into the egg white. Dip each cod fillet in the egg mixture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pan<br />Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Spray lightly with non-stick spray and cook five minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.<br /><br />Oven<br />Place cod with the side the skin was on down on an oven-safe dish. Bake in a preheated oven at 400 F for 15-20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Do not count the entire batter in your calorie content, only count half towards the total nutrition. It makes about 46-gram batter, only 22 grams is used to coat 8 oz fillets. So each 4 oz fillet has an extra 15 calories from the batter, so the total calories are then 108. <br /><br />Serve with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=205\">Jicama Fries</a> and <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=243&amp;l=en\">Tartar Sauce</a> (click on names for recipes).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the recipe\'s photo, it has been pan-fried.&nbsp; This photo displays how it looks like after being baked in the oven: <br /><img src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190413053950.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"584\" /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '244.jpg', '244_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-13', NULL, '05:28:39', 1, 0, 0, '', 1225, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd4e:229f:fd28:65ba', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '46495d113c7ccffbaaa1be970a770c200ffe90fd', '2021-02-04 20:35:44', 0, 1),
(245, 3, 'Green Beans &amp; Chicken Stir-Fry', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I love this dish at Panda Express, but I don&#039;t like all the preservatives so now I make it at home. This dish has double the protein for the same amount of calories than the one at Panda Express, so enjoy with a good conscience!', '<ol>\r\n<li>Chop ends of green beans and onion into squares or wedges. Mince garlic and ginger. Chop chicken into bite-size pieces, I like to do mine into thin strips or squares.</li>\r\n<li>Mix sauce ingredients into a small bowl set aside.</li>\r\n<li>Coat chicken in cornstarch and sesame oil. Pan-fry over medium-high heat until it is done, about 5 minutes. Set aside on a plate.</li>\r\n<li>Add green beans and onions into the pan and cook until crunchy, 4-5 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>Add chicken and sauce. Cook, until heated throughout and the sauce, has thickened.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with rice and steamed veggies. If you do not have rice wine you can substitute it for soy sauce, but be aware that the dish becomes saltier then as rice wine has a sweeter flavor. I\'d definitely recommend purchasing rice wine for a flavor more similar to Panda Express.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '245.jpg', '245_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-13', NULL, '23:59:59', 2, 0, 0, '', 999, '2001:41d0:8:445f::\n2a01:4f8:201:4228::2\n2a01:4f8:162:30e2::2\n2001:41d0:1:7558::1\n2a01:4f8:162:24d5::2\n192.99.5.228\n2a01:4f8:192:734b::2\n2a01:4f8:202:338a::2\n2a01:4f8:192:8108::2\n192.99.101.79\n2a01:4f8:190:61af::2', 1, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '8e6551028616ae23b1d46336f7732e8cb15a1163', '2021-03-13 21:16:20', 0, 1),
(246, 3, 'Egg White Crepes', 3, 'en', 'United States', 'Inspired by Crepini&#039;s Egg White Thins! These crepes are very universal. Make them sweet with berries and Greek yogurt or savory with lunch meat and mustard.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whisk together the egg whites, applesauce, flour, milk, and xanthan gum until smooth.&nbsp; If you do not have xanthan gum you can omit this, it just helps to combine the ingredients.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick cooking spray and set over low heat. I use an 8\" skillet. Pour a 1/4th cup of the batter into the skillet and spread the batter out with a tilting motion. Cook until the crepe starts to form bubbles on the top and is solid. Flip and cook for another 2 minutes. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with Greek yogurt mixed with vanilla extract and berries. Or make it savory by using lunch meat, salad, and mustard.<br /><br /><br />To store, let crepes cool and place in an airtight container or in a zip lock bag in the fridge for 3-4 days. For best consistency place paper towels or parchment paper between each crepe. Can be frozen but thaw in the fridge.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '246.jpg', '246_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '01:33:06', 0, 0, 0, '', 2796, '2600:1012:b1bf:4e8d:9009:dbd4:a84:3e0e\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9eb52b5fa337e797a461353181632ca776e78bad', '2021-02-11 02:49:24', 0, 1),
(247, 16, 'Dijon Laks', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Dijon sennep er en fin m&aring;te &aring; legge til den ekstra smaken i mat uten overfl&oslash;dig kalorier. Det fungerer spesielt godt over ovnbakt laks!', '<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Forvarm ovnen til 200 C grader.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Legg aluminiumsfolie eller bakepapir i en stekesikker form eller p<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&aring;</span>&nbsp;en stekeplate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Kutt l<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;k</span>&nbsp;og hvitl<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;</span>k i sm<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&aring;</span>&nbsp;terninger. Bland hvitl<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;k</span>, sennep og krydder sammen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Plasser laks i formen med skinnsiden ned. Topp med sennepsausen, topp med l<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&oslash;</span>k.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Bak i ovnen i 20 minutter, eller til laks er ferdig. Den er ferdig n<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&aring;</span>r den enkelt kan flakes med en gaffel.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '247.jpg', '247_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '05:39:27', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1071, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.136.113', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c8bf7d3580b5c836aaae04ebc116f6a09c73038d', '2021-02-05 02:45:47', 0, 1),
(249, 16, 'Stekt Torsk med Chili', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En deilig og rask m&aring;te &aring; lage tilapia p&aring;! V&aelig;r oppmerksom p&aring; at chilipulver er forskjellig fra cayennepepper. Bruk gjerne annen fisk som sei.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kombiner chilipulver, hvitl&oslash;kspulver (eller hakket hvitl&oslash;k) og salt i en liten bolle.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Gni fisken med krydderblandingen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tilsett olje i en panne over middels h<span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Open Sans, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">&oslash;</span></span>y varme. Legg til fisken og stek til ferdig, vend en gang, ca. 4-7 minutter, avhengig av tykkelsen p&aring; filetene. Fisken er ferdig dersom den flaker n&aring;r du trykker den lett med en gaffel.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 267px; top: 202px;\">\r\n<div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '249.jpg', '249_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '06:14:35', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1052, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'cebd475780eabe79546377ca74671bbb14f3a9b3', '2021-02-05 02:52:14', 0, 1),
(250, 16, 'Chick-fil-A Grillet kylling', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Hemmeligheten bak den velsmakende kyllingen ved Chik-fil-A er en god saltlake og et tynt kyllingbryst som gj&oslash;r at kyllingbrystet kan tilberedes jevnt.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hvis du ikke har et tynt kyllingbryst, sommerfugl det og sl&aring; det flatt. Dette trinnet er n&oslash;dvendig fordi kyllingbrystet har en ujevn form, det vil ikke komme i kontakt med pannen eller grillen for &aring; steke jevnt som for eksempel biff gj&oslash;r.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kombiner alle ingrediensene i en bolle og ha i kyllingen, la st&aring; i 15-30 minutter. Du kan dekke og sette det i kj&oslash;leskapet eller la det v&Atilde;&brvbar;re p&aring; benken for &aring; f&aring; en lunken temperatur som er klar for grillen / pannen. Etter 15-30 minutter drenerer marinaden, la kyllingbrystet hvile p&aring; et papirh&aring;ndkle eller i en kolander i et minutt eller to.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray en stekepanne med non-stick spray eller bruk en grillpanne. Grill eller stek kylling 6-8 minutter avhengig av tykkelsen p&aring; kyllingbrystet eller inntil den indre temperaturen p&aring; kyllingen n&aring;r 73 C. La kylling st&aring; 5-10 minutter f&aring;r du kutter det opp.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=251&amp;l=no\">Market Sala</a>t (klikk for oppskrift) eller p&aring; et ristet grovt hamburgerbr&oslash;d med salat, tomat og ost.<br /><br />Bare 10% av kaloriene i saltlake vil bli absorbert i kyllingbrystet.</p>\r\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 402px; top: 368px;\">\r\n<div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '250.jpg', '250_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '06:25:13', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1081, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n193.202.110.21\n2a03:2880:22ff:12::face:b00c\n2a03:2880:20ff:6::face:b00c\n2a03:2880:20ff:74::face:b00c\n2a03:2880:20ff::face:b00c\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '426085e4a9c36c3720feeaa3c991cac950615dff', '2021-02-05 02:45:51', 0, 1)
")
