(251, 16, 'Market Salat ala Chik-fil-A', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Dette er min favorittrett hos Chik-fil-A. Pr&oslash;v denne til middag i dag, du vil ikke angre!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Krutt opp gr<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;n</span>nsaker og frukt, bland.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=250&amp;l=no\">grillet Chik-fil-A grillet kyllingbryst (klikk for oppskrift)</a>, granola, traneb&aelig;r pekann<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;</span>tter, mandler, valn<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;</span>tter, stekt mandler og bl&aring;ost.<br /><br />Hvis du lager denne oppskriften p&aring; forh&aring;nd, foresl&aring;r jeg at du leser SeriousEats artikkel om hvordan du kan forhindre at eplene dine bruner her: https://www.seriouseats.com/2015/09/how-to-prevent-apple-pear-browning. html</p>\r\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 849px; top: 111px;\">\r\n<div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '251.jpg', '251_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '06:39:30', 0, 0, 0, '0', 1068, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n204.12.226.26\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'efe516f2614f62e08c6e5fe5f8cc1f402102cbf3', '2021-02-05 02:45:51', 0, 1),
(252, 16, 'Kylling og Rotgr&oslash;nnsaker Suppe', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Lett og sunt! Du er velkommen til &aring; erstatte med gr&oslash;nnsaker som ristet k&aring;l, brokkoli, gr&oslash;nne b&oslash;nner, mais eller hva som helst annet er i kj&oslash;leskapet ditt.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hakk gr&oslash;nnsakene til &oslash;nsket fasong og kyllingen i mindre biter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Stekeplate</strong><br />Tilsett ingredienser til en suppepanne. La det sm&aring;koke i 15-20 minutter. Fjern l&oslash;vbladet og server.<br /><br /><strong>I slow cooker</strong><br />Plasser alle ingrediensene i en slow cooker/crockpot og r&oslash;r for&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aring;</span> blande alt. Dekk og kok p<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aring; h</span>&oslash;yt i 3-4 timer eller p<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aring; </span>lav i 6-7 timer.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server toppet med ferske hakkede urter som koriander og v<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&aring;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">rl</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;</span>k. Ha gjerne til nyristet br<span style=\"color: #626262;\">&oslash;d</span>.</p>\r\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 557px; top: 225px;\">\r\n<div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/2/2019', '252.jpg', '252_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '07:00:03', 0, 0, 0, '0', 955, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n79.160.26.221\n204.12.226.26\n2600:8802:2f90:300:d0c3:149c:76cf:b777\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:5418:a858:b81c:9867', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'e10fb8133fa4a8bd9015202a53b062d432f8792a', '2021-02-05 02:45:52', 0, 1),
(253, 3, 'Giant Berry Smoothie Bowl', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Rolled oats in your smoothie bowl keep you fuller longer than traditional smoothie bowls based on fruits. This is because oats have fiber that helps keep your blood sugar stable and are a low GI index food. Pick any frozen berry such as blueberries, cherries, raspberries, blackberries, or a mix! You can replace bananas with equal amounts of Greek yogurt.', '<p>There are three ways of making this smoothie bowl. I\'d recommend the cooked overnight version because it yields a greater volume and is affected by the resistant starch heating/cooling cycle.&nbsp; You can substitute banana with Greek yogurt or both.&nbsp; Also, I make my oats with water but you can use unsweetened almond milk or other kinds of milk. <br /><br /><br /><strong>Overnight, recommended!</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step 1<br /></strong><br />Combine oats and 300-gram water per serving in a pot or a large microwave-safe dish.<br />Microwave for 4-5 minutes, let rest until it cools.<br />Stove, let simmer for 10-15 minutes, let stand until it cools.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 2<br /></strong><br />Cover and place in the fridge. Freeze blueberries and banana.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 3<br /></strong><br />In the morning or 6 hours later, add everything to a blender and blend until desired consistency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Overnight, cold.</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step 1<br /></strong><br />Combine oats and 200-gram water per serving in a bowl. Cover and place in the fridge overnight or 8 hours.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 2<br /></strong><br />Freeze blueberries and banana.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 3<br /></strong><br />In the morning or 8 hours later, combine everything in a blender and blend until desired consistency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Right now, more gritty consistency.</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Combine everything in a blender using 160-gram water per serving in your blender. Blend until desired consistency.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite toppings such as walnuts, banana, peanut butter, fresh berries like strawberries or raspberries.</p>\r\n<p>I recommend adding a dash of salt to your rolled oats. Salt enhances the flavor by bringing out the sweetness and nuttiness from rolled oats.<br /><br /></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '253.jpg', '253_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-14', NULL, '17:43:10', 0, 0, 0, '', 2161, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n2600:1012:b10c:e605:dc3e:7b9:b0ac:c41e\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7cdc:d45f:27a:f684', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'aa9a58df335bf2ca6674b0d25c195d9f134b6300', '2021-02-04 20:24:02', 0, 1),
(254, 3, 'Cauliflower Taco', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Looking for a great recipe for Meat Free Monday? Try Cauliflower Tacos!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. Cut the cauliflower into the desired shape. I usually do smaller florets or slices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop or puree the Chipotle Pepper In Adobo Sauce in a food processor.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add everything except the cauliflower into a bowl and mix. Add the cauliflower and toss with a Kitchen Tongs. You can also place them into a container and shake it, baby!</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay the cauliflower on a parchment or foil-covered baking sheet. Bake in the oven for 18-20 minutes until the cauliflower has a nice brown color.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in taco shells or mini tortillas. Top with your favorite taco toppings, I top mine with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=9&amp;l=en\">Quick Coleslaw Mix</a> and <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=59&amp;l=en\">Cilantro-Lime Yogurt.</a> Click on the names for the recipes.&nbsp;<br /><br />Taco Topping Ideas<br />- Fresh chopped cilantro <br />- Greek yogurt or sour cream<br />- Shredded Mexican cheese or <a href=\"../food/view_food.php?food_id=192&amp;l=en\"><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Queso </span><span class=\"recipe-directions__list--item\">Fresco </span>Mexican cheese.</a>&nbsp;<br />- Avocado or Guacamole<br />- Green onions<br />- Sliced Jalapeno<br />- Salsa or pico de gallo<br />- Corn<br />- Sliced red cabbage</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '254.jpg', '254_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-15', NULL, '23:29:41', 26, 0, 0, '', 1616, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:1012:b16c:9d86:90fa:81f3:c6e5:8f01\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f42d:b52a:c688:4fa', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '324d0517ae78e8a27debc840964708ff3cdbdfc1', '2021-02-04 19:46:27', 0, 1),
(255, 3, 'Salt &amp; Vinegar Cauliflower', 3, 'en', 'United States', 'I can&#039;t be the only one that loves salt and vinegar potato chips? This low-calorie dish mimics that flavor very well!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cauliflower into the desired size and add to a bowl. Pour over the vinegar, oil, and salt. Toss to mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay the cauliflower on a parchment or foil-covered baking sheet. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until they start to brown.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with chopped fresh parsley.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '255.jpg', '255_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-18', NULL, '04:30:57', 0, 0, 0, '', 1202, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:300:c41c:5089:c5d7:8d4c\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n114.119.156.144\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:2027:99d8:5fa:a46a', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '8883fdbe648fd8cfcc4e837b8a3bff8fbfbc7e57', '2021-02-04 21:03:53', 0, 1),
(256, 3, 'Chipotle Tofu Sliders for Sandwiches', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and easy to make!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Press the tofu, if you do not know how to follow<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=14&amp;l=en\"> this guide.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice tofu into thin slices, either lengthwise or crosswise.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients except tofu into a small bowl. Cover tofu slices with the mixture and place in the fridge to marinate for 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F. Bake tofu slices in the oven on a parchment covered cookie sheet for 20-30 minutes, flipping once.<br /><br /><strong>Pan-fried</strong><br />Heat up a skillet over medium-high and coat with non-stick spray.&nbsp; Cook tofu slices for 5 minutes on each side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve on a sandwich bread topped with your favorite toppings. Such as lettuce, spinach, tomatoes, bell peppers, cucumbers, avocado, onions, sprouts, a Greek yogurt sauce such as <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=5&amp;l=en\">Thousand Island</a> or <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=38&amp;l=en\">Chipotle Sauce</a>.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '256.jpg', '256_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-18', NULL, '22:39:31', 25, 0, 0, '', 1390, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:a9d0:7d61:58fb:d493', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '86c6dac75d86f95203b54b893f6591ab29b67e44', '2021-02-04 20:00:46', 0, 1),
(257, 3, 'Spicy Glazed Tofu', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'The chili sauce gives a spicy flavor and the sweetness from hoisin sauce balances out the spice in this perfect combination.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Press the tofu, if you do not know how to follow<a href=\"../blog/view_post.php?post_id=14&amp;l=en\"> this guide.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice tofu into thin slices, either lengthwise or crosswise.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients except tofu into a small bowl. Cover tofu slices with the mixture and place in the fridge to marinate for 30 minutes or an hour if you have the time.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven-Baked</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F. Bake tofu slices in the oven on a parchment covered cookie sheet for 20-30 minutes, flipping once.<br /><br /><strong>Pan-fried</strong><br />Heat up a skillet over medium-high and coat with non-stick spray or sesame oil.&nbsp; Cook tofu slices for 5 minutes on each side.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in a salad, as the main entree, or in sandwiches.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '257.jpg', '257_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-19', NULL, '23:06:13', 26, 0, 0, '', 1507, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '3f1a2ce7c2c4ad6e1711f90c02b92253055843e2', '2021-02-04 21:17:53', 0, 1),
(258, 3, 'Easy Shrimp &amp; Vegetables Sheet Pan', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Feel free to switch or add more vegetables such as mushrooms, green beans, asparagus. You can also use lemon pepper instead of regular black pepper.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 400 F. Mix spice mix in a small bowl, set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop veggies into the desired shape and mix with half the spice mix.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat shrimp with the remaining spice mix and set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Line a sheet pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil. Line the sheet pan with veggies and place in the oven for 10-15 minutes, until vegetable brown. Add shrimp and cook an additional 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Goes well topped with freshly grated carrots. Serve with a salad or rice.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '258.jpg', '258_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-22', NULL, '01:51:33', 0, 0, 0, '', 1076, '2600:1012:b11b:d68f:5cb9:9282:7da3:d366\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:310d:71c7:863:1eed', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '971b910c82487c4effa2a4818b7fcbe7882d431f', '2021-03-03 21:42:14', 0, 1),
(259, 3, 'Banana muffins', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Inspired by my banana bread recipe.', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat oven to 425 F. Place muffin liners into a muffin pan.</li>\r\n<li>Mash one banana and mix it with all the wet ingredients.</li>\r\n<li>Add all dry ingredients into a bowl, I like to sift them through a colander to make sure there are no lumps. Mix and make a hole in the middle. Pour the wet ingredients into the hole and fold in the dry ingredients, do not overmix. It is better that there are some lumps in the batter than overmixing it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Scoop batter into muffin liners, I use a tablespoon to make this easier. For each muffin liner, I use about 48 grams of the batter.</li>\r\n<li>Bake in the preheated oven for 7-8 minutes. Turn the heat down to 375 and bake until finished, around 7-9 more minutes.</li>\r\n</ol>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '259.jpg', '259_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-22', NULL, '02:01:07', 23, 0, 0, '', 1905, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:500:2520:dc8d:72ff:b26a\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:310d:71c7:863:1eed', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'ebd21892797e6d62eb6e252a3e27142cd0390b58', '2021-02-04 19:39:24', 0, 1),
(261, 3, 'Pasta &amp; Seasonal Roasted Vegetables', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'An easy and tasty dinner that you can customize with leftovers from the fridge. Feel free to add a source of protein such as Spicy Glazed Tofu or Chipotle Chicken.', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat oven to 425 F. Line a sheet pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil.</li>\r\n<li>Chop bell pepper, onion, and zucchini and place on the sheet pan. Lightly salt them. If desired, coat with oil. Let bake for 10-20 minutes until they are browned.</li>\r\n<li>Boil pasta after directions.</li>\r\n<li>Chop and combine tomato, garlic, basil with red wine vinegar.</li>\r\n<li>Mix pasta, veggies with the tomato, garlic, and basil sauce. Add salt and pepper to taste.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve topped with red pepper flakes, parmesan cheese, and freshly chopped carrots.<br /><br />You can also use balsamic vinegar.2-gram basil = 1 tablespoon.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '261.jpg', '261_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-22', NULL, '16:01:32', 0, 0, 0, '', 681, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:213d:6f50:1a3b:40b', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '0d1f182c06cf2d04809bd517b25139ef3d67fef0', '2021-02-04 20:50:36', 0, 1),
(262, 16, '3 Ingredient Protein Cookies', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Tired of your regular protein shake? Mix it up with these simple protein cookies. See the bottom of this recipe for different variations such as with an egg or egg white.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper or use a silicone baking mat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine ingredients, make sure to use fresh baking powder. Spread each cookie out on the baking tray using a full teaspoon of batter for each.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake in oven 8-10 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Let cool before eating for a crispier cookie. <span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">I used Optimum Nutrition Vanilla Whey in my cookies but other protein powders will also work. If you use an unflavored protein powder, add a teaspoon of vanilla extract and sweeten it to taste. </span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><br /><br /><strong>Variation of this recipe using egg whites and whole egg:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Replace apple sauce with egg white</strong><br />The batter is sticky and hard to spread on the cookie tray. Made dry, rubber texture cookies. <br />Nutritional breakdown: 137 calories, 28-gram protein, 1-gram fat, 3-gram carbs. <br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Apple sauce (20 gram) and egg white</strong><br />This created a bread consistency, it was moist and reminded me of a sponge cake. Makes a bigger serving of batter that yields about 15 cookies. <br /></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Nutritional breakdown: 147 calories, 28-gram protein, 1-gram fat, 5-gram carbs. Picture 4. </span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Replace applesauce with a whole large egg<br /></strong> The batter is sticky. However, the thinner cookies were completely crunchy.&nbsp; Thicker ones were crunchier than other recipes. Probably my favorite flavor and texture wise. Created 16 cookies. <br /></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Nutritional breakdown: 192 calories, 30-gram protein, 6-gram fat, 3-gram carbs. Picture 3.<br /></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Apple sauce (10 gram) and whole large egg</strong><br />These were the moistest cookies and with a mild sweet flavor. Makes a lot more cookies than the other recipes, about 19 of them. Picture 2. <br /></span></span><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Nutritional breakdown: 197 calories, 28-gram protein, 6-gram fat, 5-gram carbs.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span data-offset-key=\"d7l3a-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '262.jpg', '262_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-23', NULL, '02:11:48', 0, 0, 0, '', 3093, '193.202.110.21\n2600:1012:b14c:928d:1175:454f:7ef1:58fe\n2600:8802:2f90:500:b9b6:cc64:f7cf:4c4\n2600:1012:b16e:f659:edae:2fe4:2538:1d8\n2600:1012:b1bf:4e8d:edec:fa7d:c1f2:5972\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.12', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:3122:4789:a6bc:1912', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '9b46f97d7bd4b83577329a4aa704234dfb8ed97c', '2021-02-18 20:33:22', 0, 1),
(263, 3, 'Egg White Oatmeal: Never Ending Edition', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Ever wanted a GIANT bowl of something? Try this never-ending oatmeal!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make your oatmeal as you normally would. <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=13&amp;l=en\">Click for a recipe that adds even more volume to your regular oatmeal.</a> </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add two egg-whites to a glass or stainless steel bowl. M<span data-offset-key=\"979i1-0-0\">ix with an electronic mixer until it forms white stiff peaks. Start with the mixer on slow, when bubbles form you can increase the speed. <br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Gently fold egg-whites into your oatmeal. Cook in microwave or stovetop until egg-whites are fully cooked, about. 2-4 minutes. Stir every 30-60 seconds to make sure that egg-white cooks evenly. Careful that you do not overcook the eggs as they have a tendency to become rubber consistency then. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite oatmeal toppings. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '263.jpg', '263_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-24', NULL, '00:34:07', 0, 0, 0, '', 1044, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n79.160.26.221\n5.189.141.124\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4c64:f251:9716:4e70\n185.191.171.39\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:3122:4789:a6bc:1912', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'dee776be907de90b301318ea6265a652737f779b', '2021-02-04 20:18:01', 0, 1),
(264, 3, 'Sriracha Dressing', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'The all-time favorite hot sauce is taken to another level in this Greek Yogurt Dressing.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine all the ingredients in a small bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you feel like the dressing is too thick add a teaspoon of water. <br />Can be stored in an airtight container for 2-3 days in the fridge.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '264.jpg', '264_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-24', NULL, '01:24:31', 0, 0, 0, '', 895, '2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:b9b6:cc64:f7cf:4c4\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.21\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:3122:4789:a6bc:1912', '', '72c618bd9c6c07a01e97a1cd9ebb069803372231', '2021-02-19 00:15:28', 0, 1),
(265, 3, 'Thin Pizza Crust Recipe', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I can&#039;t be the only one that is tired of eating tortilla or pita pizzas... This crust is better than DiGiorno&#039;s ultra-thin pizza! Fits one 10&quot; round pizza pan. You can make it without yeast, look at the bottom of this recipe for directions.', '<ol>\r\n<li>Carefully measure out and add all ingredients to a bowl. Mix together using a spatula, once combined kneed the dough for 5 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>Let the dough rise covered in a plastic wrap for 30 minutes while the oven preheats to 425 F.</li>\r\n<li>Add a pinch of salt and roll out the dough into the desired shape using a rolling pin. It might take a bit of practice before you are able to roll it very thin, so be patient. Place on a parchment covered pizza pan or on a baking tray.</li>\r\n<li>Top with your favorite pizza toppings and bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Since this is a thin pizza crust you don\'t want to overcrowd it with toppings. If you put too much the crust will become saggy. I recommend 28-gram / 1 oz cheese per serving. Also, brushing on the sauce helps make sure you don\'t put too much.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To make it easier to roll out the dough, use parchment paper under it and a plastic wrap over the dough/</p>\r\n<p>I recommend making your pizza dough with yeast. However, if you want you can make it without. Just replace yeast with 0.5 teaspoon baking powder per serving. The dough is a bit sticker and harder to work with, but not by a lot. This is the result of a yeast-free dough:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '265.jpg', '265_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-25', NULL, '01:50:11', 0, 0, 0, '', 1416, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n2600:8802:2f90:500:2520:dc8d:72ff:b26a\n2600:8802:2f90:300:1030:2d7d:5cee:a0e8\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f169:6e23:516c:26c2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '3d37c862f48c8c12f5cf5fc862f6b501830566b6', '2021-02-04 21:17:55', 0, 1),
(266, 3, 'Cheesecake Pancakes', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious pancakes made with ricotta for extra protein and cheesecake-like texture.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Zest a lemon.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another, except the blueberries. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. <br /></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Griddle</strong><br />Preheat a griddle to 375. Use a tablespoon to pour batter onto the griddle, sprinkle with blueberries on top of pancakes. Cook until bubbles on top of your pancake burst, then flip and cook until done for about 2 more minutes.&nbsp; <br /><br /><strong>Skillet</strong><br />Place a skillet over medium heat, wait until hot before you add the batter. Use a tablespoon to pour the batter onto your skillet, sprinkle with blueberries on top of each pancake. Cook until bubbles on top of your pancake burst, then flip and cook until done for about 2 more minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Sprinkling the blueberries over pancakes helps avoid too many in one pancake and your batter from turning blue. I make 8, 4\" pancakes with this batter. Depending on your pan and/or griddle you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '266.jpg', '266_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-26', NULL, '01:15:57', 0, 0, 0, '', 1303, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n79.160.26.221\n185.191.171.3\n5.189.141.124\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:9547:d115:b5b3:4766', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'a8241fc9e00ab7592d18f6889341e100f54c9793', '2021-02-04 19:50:13', 0, 1),
(267, 3, 'Spicy Glazed Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'This is the perfect sticky, spicy, and sweet chicken recipe while remaining low-calorie.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine sauce ingredients in a bowl and set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop chicken into bite-size pieces, I like mine in thin strips. Coat with cornstarch and a pinch of salt.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place a skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until it is done, 3-5 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir sauce and add to the skillet. Cook until heated through and the sauce has thickened.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with rice, steamed veggies, or<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=125&amp;l=en\"> zoodles.</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '267.jpg', '267_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-26', NULL, '02:03:10', 2, 0, 0, '', 981, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n185.191.171.37', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:158a:29be:9848:7778', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '4d21ea491f642870ffe0d1eecafbc83528a146be', '2021-02-04 21:17:53', 0, 1),
(268, 3, 'Ranch made with Greek Yogurt', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'I Can&#039;t Believe It&#039;s Not Ranch ;)', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine all ingredients in a bowl. For best flavor let stand in fridge 15-30 minutes before serving. Add a tablespoon (15 ml)&nbsp; water per serving for a thinner consistency. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can replace 20-gram Greek yogurt with mayo for a more full-fat ranch consistency.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '268.jpg', '268_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-27', NULL, '01:30:21', 0, 0, 0, '', 735, '72.79.53.50\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f1d1:b9b8:df5f:b732', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'e81cd07f69703e6c27ba6ea3fbadb737665c41d9', '2021-03-06 11:10:09', 0, 1),
(269, 3, 'Lemon Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and easy way to cook chicken', '<ol>\r\n<li>Zest a lemon. Mix spices, zest, and lemon juice in a small bowl.</li>\r\n<li>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</li>\r\n<li>Coat chicken breast with the spice mix</li>\r\n<li>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken in the fridge after coating it with the spice mix. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '269.jpg', '269_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-27', NULL, '01:40:02', 0, 0, 0, '', 759, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n5.189.141.124\n185.191.171.21\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 1, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f1d1:b9b8:df5f:b732', '', 'b11f9326860d5e5d5fd67804b0f173450528de9a', '2021-02-04 20:40:54', 0, 1),
(270, 3, 'Daikon Radish Fries', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Daikon has 18 calories per 100-gram, making it the perfect diet food. Low-carb and delicious.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the daikon radish into thin matchsticks about 1/4 inches thick.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a large bowl mix together the spices and daikon radish. Spray canola oil (or other oil) on top and toss to evenly coat the daikon radish with spices and oil.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">Place Daikon strips in a single layer on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 30-45 minutes.&nbsp;<br /></span><br /><strong>Air-Fryer&nbsp;</strong><br />Place the daikon radish strips in a single layer in the air fryer basket and cook for 10 minutes on 350 F.&nbsp; Shake the basket halfway through. <span style=\"color: #626262;\">Cook an additional 5 minutes on 375 F.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=268&amp;l=en\">ranch</a> and topped with green onions, freshly chopped parsley, ketchup, mustard, and parmesan cheese.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '270.jpg', '270_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-27', NULL, '01:46:45', 0, 0, 0, '', 1030, '2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.189.141.124\n178.150.14.250\n185.191.171.12\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f1d1:b9b8:df5f:b732', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'eb137d1b9161dd5e6508d27c636ea47fe212bc6f', '2021-02-19 01:06:19', 0, 1),
(271, 3, 'Powdered Peanut Butter Cookies', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Makes 6 giant and 9 regular sized cookies.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper or use a silicone baking mat.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine ingredients, make sure to use fresh baking powder. Depending on your powdered peanut butter you might have to use more or less water so add it in increments. Spread each cookie thin on the baking tray using a full teaspoon of batter for each.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake in oven 10-12 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When you take them out of the oven they will be soft so let them cool before eating! You can use other sweeteners instead of the monk fruit blend I use.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '271.jpg', '271_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-29', NULL, '01:43:24', 0, 0, 0, '', 3331, '2600:8802:2f90:500:c9de:64a8:c76c:d5b1\n2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.38\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c1df:140c:be77:ce06', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2842d60630984355546776eda9e50c4d5ebfa270', '2021-02-23 04:10:44', 0, 1),
(272, 3, 'Cilantro &amp; Lime Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'An easy and tasty way to make chicken, perfect for meal prep, salads or by itself.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cilantro. Mix Worchester sauce with lime. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breast with the lime mix, cilantro, salt, and pepper to taste. </p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken it in the fridge after coating it with the spice mix. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a> </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '272.jpg', '272_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-29', NULL, '02:02:31', 0, 0, 0, '', 747, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n185.191.171.45\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:c1df:140c:be77:ce06', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'f21b6bfe7be6ea87aa560e434c4066cb6ee6622c', '2021-02-04 20:02:51', 0, 1),
(273, 3, 'Tofu Burger', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'You can swap out veggies or add more spice.', '<ol>\r\n<li>Press the tofu to make sure that you drain all the water from it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Chop onion, carrots, chipotle peppers, and bell pepper into small dices.</li>\r\n<li>Crumble the tofu into a bowl. Add the vegetables, cornstarch, salt, pepper, and combine.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Form into two patties, I like to use a 4 oz patty maker for this. Set the patties in the fridge to chill for 30 minutes, it is not necessary but I feel it is easier to handle them after they been chilled</li>\r\n<li>Pan fry or oven bake the burger:<br /><br />Cook in a pan on medium-high heat until golden. About 5-6 minutes on each side. <br /><br /><strong>&nbsp; Or<br /><br /></strong>Heat oven to 350 F, place patties on a parchment-covered baking sheet, and bake for 30 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with your favorite burger toppings.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '273.jpg', '273_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-30', NULL, '01:15:53', 26, 0, 0, '', 1199, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'ccb8b5d93a9137c45844a94c954976d6c1b6a88f', '2021-02-04 21:26:21', 0, 1),
(274, 3, 'Easy Lime Tofu', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I can&#039;t be the only one that loves to make dinner in the oven!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add soy sauce, lime juice, and sesame oil in a bowl and mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop tofu into desired bite-size pieces.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine tofu with the marinade and let marinate in the fridge for 30 minutes to an hour.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake at 400 F for 30-40 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a green salad, or with rice and vegetables.&nbsp; Goes great topped with freshly chopped cilantro.</p>\r\n<p>For the marinade, the tofu only absorbs about 1/3rd of the liquid. So only 1/3rd of the marinade towards the total calories. So each serving have 13 calories from the marinade.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '274.jpg', '274_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-30', NULL, '01:35:52', 26, 0, 0, '', 1001, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n185.191.171.18\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '2222920f44164ec60ebeb1a66e5d6826b640dd73', '2021-02-04 20:14:19', 0, 1),
(275, 3, 'Pumpkin Muffins', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Makes 3 muffins so adjust the serving to how many you&#039;d like to make.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 350 F. Place muffin liners into a muffin pan.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not overmix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into muffin liners using a spoon, I do about 50-gram batter in each.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bake for 23-30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can switch whole pastry flour for all-purpose flour. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">You can also use another sweetener than Monkfruit with erythritol</span></span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '275.jpg', '275_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-04-30', NULL, '01:44:48', 0, 0, 0, '', 1107, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:989f:c7e:3a25:e6e4\n193.202.110.21\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.35\n185.191.171.39', 0, NULL, '142.129.116.49', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '252f126de25e63ff478cc3b4fe86e155b1b30a95', '2021-02-04 21:00:24', 0, 1),
(276, 3, 'Chipotle &amp; Lime Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Chipotle Shrimp is great in tortilla&#039;s, with rice, or over pasta for a healthy and tasty dinner.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop the chipotle pepper with adobo sauce. Add chipotle peppers, lime, and spices in a bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Toss the shrimp in spice mix and let marinate for 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Pan-fried:</strong> <br />Heat a skillet over medium-high heat, add shrimp and cook until they are done, about 2-3 minutes on each side. <br />Heat a large heavy-duty or cast-iron skillet on high heat for 2 minutes. Remove shrimp from marinade. Add shrimp to pan; saut&eacute; 3 minutes or until thoroughly cooked. <br /><br /><strong>BBQ:</strong> <br />Preheat your grill to medium-high heat. Thread shrimp on skewers and grill them for about 2 minutes per side. <br /><br /><strong>Oven:</strong><br />Preheat oven to 400 F. Line a sheet pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil.&nbsp; Add shrimp and cook in the preheated oven for about 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.</p>\r\n<em>Be careful to not overcook them as shrimp cook quickly. They will turn pink and form a loose C shape when they are done. If they start curling to a tighter O shape they are overcooked.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with freshly chopped cilantro, crushed red pepper, and a squeeze of lime.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '276.jpg', '276_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-01', NULL, '01:36:47', 0, 0, 0, '', 682, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3936:5bf0:440f:21b4\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:409f:21b4:4acf:abd2', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '24189f9ce3731afeba44c05c9550655c01dcc17f', '2021-02-04 19:55:09', 0, 1),
(277, 3, 'Pumpkin Pancakes', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious mousse-like consistency makes these pancakes one of my all time favorites!', '<ol>\r\n<li>Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</li>\r\n<li>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. </span></span></li>\r\n<li><span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"><strong>Griddle</strong><br />Preheat a griddle to 375. Use a tablespoon to pour the batter onto the griddle. Cook until pancakes start to change color to a deeper brown, then flip and cook until done for about 2 more minutes.&nbsp; <br /><br /><strong>Skillet</strong><br />Place a skillet over medium heat, wait until hot before you add the batter. Use a tablespoon to pour the batter onto your skillet.</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\"> Cook until pancakes start to change color to a deeper brown, then flip and cook until done for about 2 more minutes.&nbsp; <br /></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>I make four and a half, 4\" pancakes with the batter. Depending on your pan and/or griddle you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/3/2019', '277.jpg', '277_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-03', NULL, '00:27:14', 0, 0, 0, '', 937, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7595:3952:5154:db6f', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b442b4bbdef7da20d08e6225656483e7a8bac45f', '2021-02-04 21:00:24', 0, 1),
(278, 3, 'Buffalo Cauliflower', 3, 'en', 'United States', 'Hot &amp; Delicious Roasted Cauliflower', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat oven to 425 F. Mix ketchup and hot sauce in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cauliflower into the desired size and add to a bowl. Pour over the hot sauce mixture and toss to mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay the cauliflower on a parchment or foil-covered baking sheet. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until they start to brown.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '278.jpg', '278_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-03', NULL, '18:00:58', 0, 0, 0, '', 810, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:9d37:4227:c46d:839f', '', 'fc89eb9863c3b7bef0f3cee562271d355c5cf5ca', '2021-02-04 19:41:26', 0, 1)
")
