(279, 3, 'Chili Lime Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Easy and tasty chicken that is perfect for meal prep!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix spices and lime juice in a small bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a thin chicken breast, butterfly it and pound it flat. This step is necessary because chicken breast has an uneven shape it will not make contact with the pan or grill to cook evenly as for example, steak does.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat chicken breasts with the spice mix.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spray a skillet with non-stick spray or use a grill pan. Grill or pan-fry chicken 6-8 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast or until the internal temperature on the chicken reaches 165 F. Let rest 5-10 minutes before cutting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with romaine salad, beans, rice, fresh cilantro, salsa, and sour cream or greek yogurt.&nbsp; <br /><br />If you want, you can leave the chicken in the fridge after coating it with the spice mix. I do not believe that marinating chicken breasts is helpful in flavor or keeping the meat moist. Read these two articles for more information on that: <a href=\"https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394\">https://www.thespruceeats.com/tips-for-marinating-chicken-482394</a> and <a href=\"https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling\">https://www.splendidtable.org/story/food-myths-busted-by-americas-test-kitchen-marinating-basting-and-boiling</a></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '279.jpg', '279_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-03', NULL, '18:11:15', 0, 0, 0, '', 694, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:fd87:9cdd:ec1:b8fd\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n178.150.14.250\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 1, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:9d37:4227:c46d:839f', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'b5981acb23ce11644390d32f6d893ca0c53e790b', '2021-02-04 19:53:48', 0, 1),
(280, 3, 'Pumpkin Waffles', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Adding an egg white is optional however I recommend it as it make the waffles more crispy. Makes four 4&quot; waffles (same size as Eggo waffles) or 2 regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you are using egg white, whip it until stiff peaks form and set aside. <br />Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp; <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\nCook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I make four and a half, 4\" waffles with each serving of the batter. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>\r\n<p>For crispier waffles, let sit a bit longer in the waffle maker after they are done, or leave them in the oven at 225 degrees after they are done.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '280.jpg', '280_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-03', NULL, '22:11:05', 0, 0, 0, '', 998, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4c64:f251:9716:4e70\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:681e:fe6e:cc42:38ba', '', 'b444da6783beb27fe9c55139d4c8def9b99c9069', '2021-02-04 21:03:48', 0, 1),
(281, 3, 'Carrot Fries', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'I love to use rainbow carrots for a stunning looking dish!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the carrots into thin matchsticks about 1/4 inches thick.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In a large bowl mix together the spices and carrots. Spray canola oil (or other oil) on top and toss to evenly coat the carrots with spices and oil.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong><br />Place the carrot strips in a single layer on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 15-20 minutes on 425 F, flip once. <br /><br /><strong>Air fryer</strong><br />Place the carrot strips in a single layer in the basket and cook for 10 minutes on 375 F. Shake the basket halfway through. For a crispier result increase the air frier to 400 F during the last 5 minutes of the cooking time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve topped with green onions, freshly chopped parsley, ketchup, mustard, and parmesan cheese.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '281.jpg', '281_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-03', NULL, '22:33:00', 0, 0, 0, '', 865, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.138.25', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:681e:fe6e:cc42:38ba', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '493e9142e588ed80bd104742db582dc15dda970f', '2021-02-04 19:45:10', 0, 1),
(282, 3, 'Pumpkin Frozen Yogurt', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Inspired by Halo Top&#039;s pumpkin flavor', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>If using Guar Gum</strong>: Mix half the milk with Guar Gum using a hand mixer. Then add everything else and mix for a couple of minutes.<br /><br /><strong>If omitting Guar Gum</strong>:<br />Mix together the ingredients using a hand mixer on medium speed for a couple of minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>If using Guar Gum</strong>: Leave in the fridge for an hour to allow Guar Gum to fully work. Then pour into a ready ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer\'s instructions.<br /><br /><strong>If&nbsp; omitting Guar gum</strong>: <br />Pour into a ready ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer\'s instructions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You can omit the Guar Gum &amp; Soy Lecithin but I find that it helps to keep the frozen yogurt softer and gives more volume.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If you do not have an ice cream maker you can use one of these three options. It will not yield the same result but still delicious:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">Freeze the mixture until semi-frozen in \"blender friendly sizes\" and then use a blender to get the right consistency.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">Freeze the mixture in a container that you stir every 30 minutes for around 2 hours.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">Use ice cream molds</li>\r\n</ol>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '282.jpg', '282_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-04', NULL, '16:27:14', 0, 0, 0, '', 742, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '654cb0ff06808a0784171880f71f649af0012aa4', '2021-02-04 20:59:38', 0, 1),
(283, 3, 'Waffles', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'I use a mini waffle iron, but it makes enough batter for two regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whip egg white until stiff peaks form and set aside. <br />Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp; <span data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\"><span data-text=\"true\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker. </span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\nCook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I make five and a half, 4\" waffles. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</p>\r\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: -20px; top: 316px;\">\r\n<div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '283.jpg', '283_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-04', NULL, '16:49:39', 0, 0, 0, '', 1150, '2600:1012:b167:83dd:5d5e:969f:c98:2a8d\n2600:8802:2f90:700:c9de:64a8:c76c:d5b1\n2600:1012:b11b:d68f:5cb9:9282:7da3:d366\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:1012:b10e:97e1:89e:4631:8452:cfb8', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', '', 'f2dbe3bddb236028f0a1f173bb863cde9e25552d', '2021-03-08 04:49:27', 0, 1),
(284, 3, 'Microwave Chocolate Sauce', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Let cool before eating for a thicker sauce.', '<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix everything into a large microwave-safe bowl.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Microwave for 2 minutes for a thinner consistency or 2 minutes and 30 seconds for a thicker consistency, stop to stir every 30 sec. Watch the sauce as it might turn into a brownie-like consistency if it is microwaved too long. If this happens, add a small amount of water and stir it back to liquid again.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir in vanilla extract.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Can be served warm but I prefer to let it cool for an hour in the fridge so it becomes thicker.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '284.jpg', '284_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-05', NULL, '00:32:47', 0, 0, 0, '', 955, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n5.255.253.73', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '508a470adf8cd16af5ecd2b97f097acdd007ed0a', '2021-02-04 20:50:15', 0, 1),
(285, 3, 'Parsley and Lemon Precooked Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'The perfect summer dish. No cooking involved when using precooked shrimp. Easy, quick, and tasty.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop fresh parsley. Mix with spices, lemon juice, and red wine vinegar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat pre-cooked shrimp with marinade and let marinate in the fridge for at least 3 hours, up to 24 hours.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with a green salad, as finger food, with cold pasta,&nbsp; rice, or with steamed vegetables.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '285.jpg', '285_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-05', NULL, '04:48:05', 0, 0, 0, '', 675, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:7eee\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n185.191.171.45', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:99b:978f:f583:5d4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fe753ac15b2f75fd0d443d7917caafde29568e8a', '2021-02-04 20:47:55', 0, 1),
(286, 3, 'Jalapeno &amp; Tomato Dip', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'The perfect dip to raw veggies or tortilla chips', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place veggies in a food processor and pulse until finely chopped.&nbsp; You might want to drain the liquid in the coriander if there is too much so your dip does not get too runny.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix greek yogurt, veggies, paprika, and a pinch of salt in a bowl. Let stand 30 minutes in the fridge before serving.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '286.jpg', '286_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-05', NULL, '23:47:23', 0, 0, 0, '', 697, '2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:1012:b148:a2c8:2d40:c401:3032:cf91\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:fca7:fd7a:cec7:d6', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '79d4d9f01d35c9bc8db2767d74d34ef857ca7521', '2021-02-19 00:14:55', 0, 1),
(287, 3, 'Sparkling Iced Tea', 6, 'en', 'United States', 'Perfect summer drink', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brew tea and let chill.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix tea with equal parts of sparkling water or soda. Add sweetener to taste.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with fresh lime or lemon juice.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/7/3/2019', '287.jpg', '287_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-05-07', NULL, '22:58:05', 0, 0, 0, '', 778, '79.161.62.47\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n185.191.171.19\n178.150.14.250\n114.119.132.43\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:7c3c:71e8:3b56:4b9', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'a241384499f932e1477849058c70ae053cc1205c', '2021-03-02 22:26:25', 0, 1),
(288, 3, 'Protein Powder Mug Cake', 5, 'en', 'United States', 'Add up to 10-grams cocoa powder for a deeper flavor. As written it has a mild cocoa flavor. Sweetener is not necessary but it can be added depending on how sweet you like your cake!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add all dry ingredients into a cereal sized bowl or big mug, mix well.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add applesauce and milk, mix.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Microwave 2 minutes and 30 seconds stopping after 1-2 minutes to check if done.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with whipped cream, ice cream, or fresh berries.&nbsp;<br /><br />I used ON 100% Whey but other whey/casein-based protein powders should also work.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '288.jpg', '288_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-07', NULL, '23:02:53', 0, 0, 0, '', 1242, '2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n185.191.171.40\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '1be40b78a8cf905a3e4123cba03c964978e32be6', '2021-02-19 01:43:27', 0, 1),
(289, 3, 'Jalapeno Dip', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'The regular cilantro gets a spicy twist with this dip!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Place garlic and jalapeno in a food processor and pulse until finely chopped.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Mix all the other ingredients into the food processor or a bowl. Let stand 30 minutes in the fridge before serving.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '289.jpg', '289_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-08', NULL, '23:30:37', 0, 0, 0, '', 578, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:14ea:4d61:b698:f383\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n114.119.151.208', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:55ec:84e3:28c1:2730', '', '6a325c13b4eb74e34e54a3a48c0375a1d5af2afe', '2021-02-04 20:32:14', 0, 1),
(290, 3, 'Cold Asian Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious way to flavor your precooked shrimp.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop cilantro and scallions. Mix together with all ingredients except shrimp.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat precooked shrimp in marinade and let stand in the fridge at least for 15-30 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in a salad, on lettuce leaves, with pasta, or on skewers.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '290.jpg', '290_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-08', NULL, '23:40:22', 0, 0, 0, '', 667, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:55ec:84e3:28c1:2730', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6edb40d3f2e8165358f671384c72bb389bd2d1d5', '2021-02-04 20:04:16', 0, 1),
(291, 3, 'Crispy Waffles', 1, 'en', 'United States', 'Follow up from my regular waffle recipe for crispier waffles. I use a mini waffle iron, but it makes enough batter for two regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Whip egg white until stiff peaks form and set aside.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #626262;\" /><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\" data-offset-key=\"6ovvf-0-0\">Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Cook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack. You might want to leave the waffle in the waffle maker longer than the regular cooking time for a crispier waffle.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are not eating them right away you can keep them warm and crispy in the oven at 225 F after cooking. If you are making them for another day or a few hours later you can re-heat them in a toaster.<br /><br />Feel free to add 0.5 teaspoon cinnamon and/or a teaspoon vanilla extract.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '291.jpg', '291_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-10', NULL, '01:19:52', 0, 0, 0, '', 1289, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n178.150.14.250\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4c64:f251:9716:4e70\n185.191.171.42\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c40f1092fd5b1d94ae1fd27deb597e8ce77d9f05', '2021-02-04 20:06:41', 0, 1),
(292, 3, 'Chinese Dipping Sauce', 8, 'en', 'United States', 'For lettuce wraps, Potstickers or Gyozas.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop scallions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/6/3/2019', '292.jpg', '292_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-10', NULL, '01:31:14', 2, 0, 0, '', 966, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n79.160.26.221\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', '', '9f354d6b8665746ed80f1b495eb19a342306ae63', '2021-02-04 19:55:08', 0, 1),
(293, 3, 'Chinese Chicken Lettuce Wrap (P.F Chang&#039;s)', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'I&#039;ve heard that traditionally P.F Chang&#039;s uses oyster sauce in their lettuce wrap. In this recipe, I use hoisin sauce to make it easier and quicker.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Chop onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, onions, scallions, and water chestnuts into small dices.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\nMix sauce ingredients in a bowl and set aside.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Cook chicken in a skillet over medium-high heat.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Towards the end of the cooking time add onion, bell pepper, mushroom, and chestnuts. Cook for 4 minutes or until chicken is done</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add sauce over chicken and let it heat up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve over lettuce wraps and dipping sauce. Recipe for dipping sauce here:&nbsp;<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=292&amp;l=en\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=292&amp;l=en</a><br /><br />It might seem like a small amount of sauce for such a big serving, but the sauce should only cover the meat and veggies and not overflow the lettuce wraps.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '293.jpg', '293_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-10', NULL, '01:39:14', 2, 0, 0, '', 1023, '72.79.53.50\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n2600:1012:b10c:e605:dc3e:7b9:b0ac:c41e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:cd1c:4bd4:187:acd4', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bc4b6d24637c7decdb0a551e4069c394d8e2b9c2', '2021-03-06 11:10:11', 0, 1),
(294, 3, 'Baked Meatballs From Turkey or Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Meatballs without eggs or breadcrumbs. You can substitute ground chicken for ground turkey or beef.', '<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Preheat oven to 400 F. </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Dice </span>the vegetables into small pieces.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Cover a baking sheet with parchment paper.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Mix spices and cornstarch in a bowl. Add ground chicken, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and mix. Add water in increments of one tablespoon until the meat is slightly sticky.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Shape meatballs using a spoon and place them on top of the baking sheet. </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Bake in the oven for10-15 minutes or until done.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with<a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=125&amp;l=en\"> zoodles,</a> <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=153&amp;l=en\">quick pasta sauce,</a> a salad, or mashed potatoes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><br />Each serving makes a total of 202-gram meatballs shaped into 8 regular sized meatballs.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">You can substitute zucchini and mushroom for other vegetables like bell peppers or carrots.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '294.jpg', '294_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-11', NULL, '00:56:08', 23, 0, 0, '', 947, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:20fd:5810:1b53:a51b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:449a:e679:2d97:eac3\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n178.150.14.250\n185.191.171.5\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:203e:fbab:a807:884', '', 'b23b6e306defcca22cb3e68af93c165319225373', '2021-02-04 19:39:27', 0, 1),
(295, 3, 'Jell-O Mousse', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Pick any sugar free flavored gelatin powder and make it into a high protein mousse. My favorite is raspberry and strawberry.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons of water and microwave it for 40-50 seconds. Whisk Jell-O and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add greek yogurt and Jell-O into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer for about 2-4 minutes, you want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '295.jpg', '295_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-12', NULL, '23:46:53', 0, 0, 0, '', 979, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'c92952ae3051075b85f4700a309c8dfacadb0d37', '2021-02-04 20:34:33', 0, 1),
(296, 3, 'Chocolate Mousse', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'The ultimate chocolate fix that fits your macros!', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bloom your gelatin in a little cold water, about one-two tablespoons. In a separate bowl heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons of water and microwave it for 40-50 seconds. Whisk gelatin and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Add greek yogurt, sugar to taste, cocoa, and gelatin into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer, for about 2-4 minutes. You want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.<br /><br />Blooming helps completely dissolve the gelatin.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '296.jpg', '296_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-13', NULL, '00:02:00', 0, 0, 0, '', 1821, '2600:1012:b127:c1ce:6913:c86d:5881:4489\n2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '5749538d6452b8cd80c9889350d056cde74dd161', '2021-02-19 00:14:35', 0, 1),
(297, 3, 'Lemon Mousse, Protein Edition', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'My all-time favorite mousse.', '<ul style=\"color: #626262;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Bloom your gelatin in a little cold water, about one-two tablespoons. In a separate bowl heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons of water and microwave it for 40-50 seconds. Whisk gelatin and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Zest lemon. Add greek yogurt, sugar substitute to taste, lemon juice, lemon zest, and gelatin into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer, for about 2-4 minutes. You want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use fresh lemon juice! Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.<br /><br />Blooming helps completely dissolve the gelatin.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '297.jpg', '297_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-13', NULL, '00:09:15', 0, 0, 0, '', 1160, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '29d48af82f610a4418a6c3c80083d214c3f5e00b', '2021-02-04 20:43:18', 0, 1),
(298, 3, 'Carrot Cake Waffles', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'A delicious way to add more volume to your regular waffles. Makes 6 mini-waffles or two regular waffles using 1/3 cup batter each.', '<ul style=\"color: #626262;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Grate the carrot. Whip egg white until stiff peaks form and set aside.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Cook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I make five to six 4\" waffles. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">For crispier waffles check out this recipe:&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=291&amp;l=en\">https://cicolife.net/recipes/view_recipe.php?recipe_id=291&amp;l=en</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Feel free to add 0.5 teaspoon cinnamon and/or a teaspoon vanilla extract.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '298.jpg', '298_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-13', NULL, '01:33:36', 0, 0, 0, '', 685, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4c64:f251:9716:4e70', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:f902:fc6c:8a1:5439', '', '512563ae528f844bb6c9f6218c7d5c7334d32a2c', '2021-02-04 19:43:58', 0, 1),
(299, 3, 'Shredded Chicken Breast', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Great for meal prep, salads, tacos, or any other occasion.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>In a pot</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place chicken breast in a pot and fill with enough water to cover it (about one inch of water above the chicken). Add spices or vegetables, I use 0.25 teaspoon salt, dash pepper, and/or bay leaf. Place the pot over medium-high heat and let boil for 10-20 minutes depending on the thickness of your chicken breast. The internal temperature of the thickest part should reach 165 F.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190515125651.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"282\" /></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Slow cooker&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place chicken breast in your slow cooker. Fill with 0.25 cup water or until the chicken breast is slightly covered. You can use chicken broth instead of water. Add salt, pepper, and/or a bay leaf. Cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 7-8 hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190515125525.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"346\" /></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>After chicken is done</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #626262;\">Once done let it cool on a plate or cutting board for a few minutes, but not too long!&nbsp; Shred with a fork and pack away in an airtight container.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #626262;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019/3_190515125739.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"394\" /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Adjust the amount of chicken you use for accurate calorie content. Stays fresh in the fridge for 2-3 days and in the freezer for 2-3 months in airtight containers.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '299.jpg', '299_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-15', NULL, '00:45:08', 0, 0, 0, '', 817, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n79.160.26.221\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:a44d:8375:25b9:ce3c', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'bb67aa011f1a034d0a39f5d6fc81ffe02203f2a7', '2021-02-04 21:03:53', 0, 1),
(300, 3, 'Protein Waffles', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Delicious and easy way to hit those macro goals!', '<ul style=\"color: #626262;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Whip one of the egg whites (33 gram) until stiff peaks form and set aside.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add all dry ingredients to a bowl and all wet ingredients to another. Mix each separately.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In the bowl with dry ingredients make a hole in the middle of the flour mix and pour the liquid in. Carefully combine the ingredients, do not over mix just combine until there is no longer any dry flour left. Fold in the egg white until mixed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Let stand 5 minutes so the gluten develops and the batter gets thicker.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Cook according to your waffle makers directions. Let waffles rest on a cooling rack.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I make 9 four-inch waffles. Depending on your waffle maker you might have to use non-stick spray. Calculate that into your total nutrition value.</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/4/3/2019', '300.jpg', '300_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-16', NULL, '06:58:38', 0, 0, 0, '', 1000, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2600:8802:2f90:300:9dce:2767:ef8b:6e0b\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:d0c3:149c:76cf:b777\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:1012:b15a:eb94:d0cd:879f:b37:6b27\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4ded:4402:a1c8:a12e\n2600:8802:2f90:300:4c64:f251:9716:4e70', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:8874:f0b7:5e89:5801', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '4500228b6895866ae5102022f53475d770185cc8', '2021-02-04 20:55:22', 0, 1),
(301, 3, 'Spicy Cold Shrimp', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'A great marinade for pre-cooked shrimp.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all ingredients except shrimp. Pour over shrimp and let marinate in the fridge for 30+ minutes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve in a salad, on lettuce leaves, with pasta, or on skewers.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '301.jpg', '301_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-16', NULL, '07:05:49', 0, 0, 0, '', 630, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n193.202.110.21\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n185.191.171.18\n185.191.171.25', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:8874:f0b7:5e89:5801', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '8634669f4d93b7e2318bd458e2ee5f6b5091de09', '2021-02-04 21:17:52', 0, 1),
(302, 3, 'Pasta &amp; Chicken Sauce in Slow Cooker', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Hearty and healthy tomato-based sauce.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop onion, bell pepper, and mushroom.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix all the ingredients in a two-quart slow cooker. Cook on high for 3-4 hours or on low for 7-8 hours.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Serve with pasta or <a href=\"view_recipe.php?recipe_id=125&amp;l=en\">zoodles</a> topped with freshly chopped basil or parsley.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '302.jpg', '302_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-17', NULL, '01:18:55', 22, 0, 0, '', 1025, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n178.150.14.250\n185.191.171.40\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:e0ac:429d:1aa1:dad6', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', 'fdf507a69a7898e861d08b96a02cd25b51e61e83', '2021-02-04 20:50:35', 0, 1),
(303, 3, 'Pumpkin Mousse, Protein Edition', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'Great high protein dessert', '<ul style=\"color: #626262;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Bloom your gelatin in a little cold water, about one-two tablespoons. In a separate bowl heat enough water to mix the gelatin in. I do 2-3 tablespoons of water and microwave it for 40-50 seconds. Whisk gelatin and water until dissolved, let it cool until it reaches room temperature.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add greek yogurt, sugar substitute to taste, pumpkin puree, and gelatin into a mixing bowl. Mix well with an electric mixer, for about 2-4 minutes. You want to whip as much air as possible into the mousse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #000000;\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pour into a 2-cup sized container and let cool in the fridge for 1-2 hours.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Stays well in the fridge for up to 36 hours.<br /><br /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #626262;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Blooming helps completely dissolve the gelatin.&nbsp;</span></p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '303.jpg', '303_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-17', NULL, '01:25:13', 0, 0, 0, '', 1113, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:7eee\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.138.25', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:e0ac:429d:1aa1:dad6', '', '62c2f131e0a29abb04a69669d2d2cc0554b24794', '2021-02-04 21:03:41', 0, 1),
(304, 3, 'Troll-Cream', 4, 'en', 'United States', 'A classic Norwegian dessert usually made with Lingonberry.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Puree the berries in a small food processor or by hand using a fork.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whip the egg white until stiff white peaks forms. Add berries and sugar and continue to whip for 4-5 more minutes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Can be eaten as it is, set cold for 4 hours, or frozen for up to 4 hours. When you freeze it the texture becomes more crunchy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Use pasteurized and safe to eat raw egg whites.<br /><br />You can use other berries such as blueberries, blackberries, or raspberries.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/5/3/2019', '304.jpg', '304_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-17', NULL, '01:32:55', 23, 0, 0, '', 1689, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n2a01:4f8:190:7382::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2600:8802:2f90:300:503f:a07c:3ae7:e574\n2600:1012:b15a:eb94:d0cd:879f:b37:6b27\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n79.160.26.221\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:e0ac:429d:1aa1:dad6', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '6da6563d21d70a3ee61a29625ac637e02dcafa2b', '2021-02-04 21:26:22', 0, 1),
(305, 3, 'Zesty Orange Chicken', 2, 'en', 'United States', 'Use a fresh orange for best flavor', '<ol>\r\n<li style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 1.6; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p>Chop vegetables and chicken into bite-size pieces. I like to do mine into thin strips or squares.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 1.6; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p>Zest orange and mix sauce ingredients into a small bowl set aside.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 1.6; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p>Coat chicken in cornstarch. Pan-fry over medium-high heat until it is done, about 5 minutes. Set aside on a plate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 1.6; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p>Add all vegetables except scallions and cook until crunchy, 4 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 1.6; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p>Add chicken, scallions, and sauce. Cook, until heated throughout and the sauce has thickened for about 3 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serve with rice and steamed veggies. Top with red pepper flakes.&nbsp; Feel free to add other vegetables such as snow peas or green beans.&nbsp;</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/3/2019', '305.jpg', '305_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-05-18', NULL, '01:31:07', 2, 0, 0, '', 1194, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:300:2dcb:f179:18b4:333e\n173.208.206.50\n2600:8802:2f90:300:797f:ae4:27e0:66b7\n2a01:7e01::f03c:91ff:febd:36fc\n79.160.26.221\n178.150.14.250\n185.191.171.24\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n114.119.156.144', 0, NULL, '2605:e000:6140:f100:b494:4a3e:b492:17ea', 'E-mail not sent to administrators', '047293a4f00ce0371d8e0071b10ae62204810fba', '2021-02-04 21:26:24', 0, 1),
(306, 1, 'Torsk i form med gr&oslash;nnsaker', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Torsk grillet i en form sammen med gr&oslash;nnsaker er noe av det sunneteste man f&aring;r. Server med fullkornpasta og du har en veldig god middag.', '<p>Denne retten har et veldig lavt innhold av fett og karbohydrater. &Oslash;nsker du &aring; kutte mer p&aring; kalorier kan du redusere mengden pasta.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Sett p&aring; ovnen p&aring; 200 grader.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Legg torskefilet i en form.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Legg gr&oslash;nnsakene rundt torskefileten. Hvis du ikke liker at det kommer fiskesmak p&aring; gr&oslash;nnsakene kan du legge dem i en annen form, eventuelt skille fisk og gr&oslash;nnsaker ved aleminiumsfolie.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Sett formen i ovnen. Fisken og gr&oslash;nnsakene skal steke i 30 minutter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>N&aring;r det er g&aring;tt 10 minutter setter du p&aring; en kjele med vann. N&aring;r denne koker har du i pasta. Pastaen skal koke i 7 minutter.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Serveres rykende varmt med god samvittighet!</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/1/2019', '306.jpg', '306_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-11-11', NULL, '15:30:15', 0, 0, 0, '', 185, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n79.160.26.221\n204.12.226.26\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '79.160.26.221', '', '6f8d18ae1b441f68c8df3904060feb6660a831d4', '2021-02-05 02:38:25', 0, 1),
(307, 1, 'Smoothie', 7, 'no', 'Norway', 'Smoothie er perfekt for varme dager og inneholder ikke mye sukker.', '<p>Ha alt i en blender og miks sammen.</p>\r\n<p>Server i glass.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/7/1/2019', '307.jpg', '307_thumb_278x156.jpg', '', '2019-11-11', NULL, '18:42:40', 0, 5, 0, '', 273, '204.12.226.26\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2', 0, NULL, '79.160.26.221', '', 'd6a18226e07b470c9125d42bbf1cbf59b564fc42', '2021-01-14 19:44:09', 0, 1),
(308, 1, 'Svinekoteletter i stekeovn med wok chinese', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'Svinekoteletter og wokblanding i ownen gj&oslash;r seg selv. Det tar litt tid &aring; steke svinekotelettene, men det er verd det.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Forvarm oven til 180 grader.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sett inn svinekotelettene i en form inn i ovnen. De skal steke i 60 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>N&aring;r det er g&aring;tt 30 minutter setter du inn wok-blandingen i ovnen. Den skal steke i 30 minutter p&aring; 180 grader. Sett p&aring; vann til pastaen. Pastaen skal koke i 8-11 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Obs! Ikke spis fettet p&aring;svinekotelettene, det inneholder inzane mye d&aring;rlige kalorier.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/1/2019', '308.jpg', '308_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-11-12', NULL, '19:11:13', 0, 0, 0, '', 271, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n79.160.26.221\n204.12.226.26\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '79.160.26.221', '', '241f4c4d818500b4fefe3bb614c366ab7b4b71a8', '2021-02-05 02:38:26', 0, 1),
(309, 1, 'Omelett med kyllingkj&oslash;ttp&oslash;lse', 1, 'no', 'Norway', 'En deilig frokost med omelett og kyllingkj&oslash;ttp&oslash;lser.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Visp sammen eggehvite og egg. Ha i en spiseskje vann pr egg. Kutt opp p&oslash;lsene i passende biter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stek p&oslash;lsene slik at de er gjennomstekt. Stek omeletten, n&aring;r den er gylden har du p&aring; pepper og legger p&oslash;lsebitene i.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Server med br&oslash;d, agurk, paprika og tomat.</p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/1/1/2019', '309.jpg', '309_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-11-14', NULL, '15:21:18', 0, 0, 0, '', 264, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2600:8802:2f90:500:847e:609e:f0f:1af6\n204.12.226.26\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n79.160.26.221\n89.8.18.209\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '79.160.26.221', '', 'e915c682796f772cc6bc9e6e4777b67c90f6e929', '2021-02-05 02:20:38', 0, 1),
(310, 1, '&Oslash;rret, wokmiks og pasta', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En middag med mye proteiner.', '<p>Dagen f&oslash;r du skal lage denne retten tar du opp fisken og legger den i kj&oslash;leskapet.</p>\r\n<p>Sett ovnen p&aring; 200 grader. Finn frem en form hvor du har s&oslash;lvfolie i. Legg fileen i s&oslash;lvfolien. Lag en annen avdeling i samme formen hvor du har wokmiksen, eventuelt bruk en ekstra form. Fileen og wokmiksen skal steke i 30 minutter.</p>\r\n<p>Sett p&aring; vann og ha i pasta. Denne skal koke i 7-11 minutter, les pakningsveiledningen. </p>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/1/2019', '310.jpg', '310_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-11-14', NULL, '19:05:08', 0, 0, 0, '', 262, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n2a01:4f8:161:6271::2\n79.160.26.221\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n89.8.18.209\n185.191.171.39\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '79.160.26.221', '', '7ed83d6b05ce8f5a208c5b75450e3ebd33cbd93d', '2021-02-05 02:38:25', 0, 1),
(311, 1, 'Kyllingfilet, gr&oslash;nnsaker og ris', 2, 'no', 'Norway', 'En veldig god rett med mye gode proteiner.', '<p>Dagen f&oslash;r du skal lage denne retten m&aring; du ta opp to kyllingfileter fra fryseboksen og til kj&oslash;leskapet.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 1</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sett ovnen p&aring; 200 grader. Finn frem s&oslash;lvfolie og legg det i en form. Ha i to kyllingfileter i formen. Disse skal bakes i 45 minutter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Steg 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sett p&aring; to kjeler med vann. En til ris og en til gr&oslash;nnsakene. Risen skal koke i 10 minutter, og gr&oslash;nnsakene skal bare ha et raskt oppkok.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '_uploads/recipes/_image_uploads/2/1/2019', '311.jpg', '311_thumb_278x156.png', '', '2019-11-16', NULL, '15:50:01', 0, 0, 0, '', 170, '2600:8802:2f90:500:535:8a11:f8ca:9838\n79.160.26.221\n2a01:4f8:161:6271::2\n2600:8802:2f90:300:3448:9b54:92cd:5131\n178.150.14.250\n2a01:4f8:161:7181::2\n2001:41d0:1004:60b::', 0, NULL, '79.160.26.221', '', '0d6237a8b7b4fcf981e847e4741efc384265a9a6', '2021-02-05 02:35:28', 0, 1)
")
